                <h3><?php _e('Find &amp; Replace', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <p><?php _e('Bulk find/replace across a table\'s entries, shipped end-to-end in the #538 slices. From Gravity Tables > All Tables, hover a table row and click the "Find / Replace" row action. The workflow is two-phase: first you enter the text to find and the plugin reports the match count via the gt_find_matches preview endpoint ("N matches found"); then you enter the replacement and confirm, and gt_apply_replace writes the changes back to the underlying Gravity Forms entries through GFAPI::update_entry. Both endpoints require the administrator (manage_options) capability and a valid nonce. Matching is exact-substring; the TC_Find_Replace_Service API also supports column scoping and case-sensitivity, which the row-action UI keeps at their defaults today (all text columns, case-sensitive) — a richer modal with a column-scope picker is tracked as follow-up work.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></p>
