                <p><?php _e('Three external-source services exist in the codebase — TC_JSON_Source_Service, TC_Airtable_Field_Mapper, and an API key store (TC_API_Key_Service) — each with its own test contract pinning the include. None of them are wired into the table builder UI today: there is no "Add External Source" path, no Airtable/Notion connection screen, and no Settings → API Keys panel for credentials. Same orphan-with-test-contract pattern as multi-sort / skeleton / bulk-migration-bundle / AI tools (see the v4.7.156 / v4.7.158 / v4.7.162 / v4.7.163 changelog). All tables today come from Gravity Forms entries — registered_table_types defaults to ["gravity", "merged"] (verified in includes/class-tc-shortcode.php). Wiring up external sources properly is roadmap work; the service files are kept in place so they can be invoked from PHP and so the test suite stays green.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></p>
