            <div id="permission-troubleshooting" class="gt-docs-section">
                <h2><?php _e('Permission Troubleshooting', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h2>
                <p><?php _e('If users with correct roles still hit access errors, work through these steps:', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></p>

                <ol>
                    <li><?php _e('Verify user roles in WordPress → Users.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><?php _e('In the table builder, scroll to the User Permissions feature group and confirm the user\'s role is in the "Table Access Control" multi-select. (Earlier versions of this guide said "General tab → Access Control" — that was misleading; the control lives in the main table builder area, not in a field-level tab.)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><?php _e('Look for multiple active table configurations targeting the same form. Older "AJS Trucking Toolkit" sites had a known issue here — only one active table per form/role.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><?php _e('Enable WordPress debug logging (define WP_DEBUG and WP_DEBUG_LOG in wp-config.php) and watch wp-content/debug.log while reproducing the issue.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><?php _e('Test with different user roles to isolate whether the issue is role-specific or universal.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ol>

                <h3><?php _e('Common Causes', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('JavaScript querySelector errors', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> - <?php _e('Often a downstream symptom of a backend permission denial.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Intermittent "Access denied" messages', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> - <?php _e('Multiple matching table configurations being selected non-deterministically.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>
