                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.4.1 — Data Bars: RTL bar-direction flip', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Data bars now fill from the right in RTL mode (#1737)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('In RTL mode the in-cell data bar fill now grows from the logical start (right edge) rather than the physical left edge. A two-rule override in frontend-rtl.css scoped to .gt-rtl .gt-table tbody td with data-gt-bar-pct sets right: 0 and left: auto, cancelling the inset shorthand from frontend.css. The RTL stylesheet is already conditionally enqueued by TC_RTL_Service and the .gt-rtl class is already applied to the wrapper, so no JS or PHP changes are required.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.4.0 — Data Bars: SSP support', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Data bars in server-side-pagination mode (#1735)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('In-cell data bars now render in SSP tables. The server computes a page-scoped per-column maximum via TC_Data_Bars_Service::parse_numeric and returns it as bar_maxes in the AJAX response. The JS loadEntriesServerSide stores the map in _sspBarMaxes; renderSSPEntries calls computeDataBarParams per numeric cell and emits data-gt-bar-pct plus CSS variable attributes on the td element, using the same underlay driven by the existing ::after rule.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.3.0 — Data Bars: pivot view support', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Data bars in pivot view (#1734)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Aggregate columns in pivot-view tables now render in-cell data bars. A new computePivotBarMaxes method scans pivot rows for the page-scoped maximum of each bar-enabled numeric aggregate column. renderPivotRowsHtml emits data-gt-bar-pct and CSS variable attributes on each qualifying cell using the same attribute surface as the regular data-bar path, so the existing ::after CSS underlay drives the fill without any markup change inside the cell. The group-by column is always skipped; non-numeric, disabled, and zero-domain columns emit no bars.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.2.0 — Data Bars: server-supplied filtered-set column max', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Filtered-set column max for Data Bars (#1733)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Data bars now scale against the maximum value across ALL rows matching the current filters, not just the rows on the current page. The server computes one MAX query per enabled numeric bar column (reusing the same WHERE clause as the pagination count), attaches the result as bar_column_maxes in the AJAX response, and the JS layer merges it into the bar max map so every page of results uses a consistent scale. Pro-gated.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.1.1 — Data bars in legacy direct-load fallback', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Data bars in FALLBACKJS2 rows (#1732)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('The legacy inline direct-load path (loadDirectData) now computes a page-scoped barMaxes map and emits data-gt-bar-pct / CSS variable attributes on bar-enabled numeric cells, matching the output of the normal renderTextCellHtml path. Zero values emit a zero-width bar; non-numeric values emit no attribute; values above the page max clamp to 100.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.1.0 — Frontend bundle on by default', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Bundle default ON (#1658)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('The consolidated JS bundle (~4 requests) is now the default for all installs. Previously the feature flag defaulted to false, requiring manual opt-in via Settings to cut ~55 individual script handles down to ~4. Installs with no explicit setting in the database now automatically use the bundle. Sites that have already set the flag to false continue to load individual handles unchanged. A related silent bug where inline table-config scripts were dropped in bundle mode (WordPress ignores inline scripts attached to un-enqueued handles) is also fixed.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v7.0.3 — EU-decimal and locale numeric parse', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Locale-aware numeric parsing (#1736)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Numbers in EU format (e.g. "1.234,56" meaning 1234.56) now parse correctly in column totals and data bars. The fix applies to both the JS gtParseNumeric helper and its PHP mirror TC_Data_Bars_Service::parse_numeric. The heuristic: a separator followed by exactly 3 digits is a thousands grouping character; 1 or 2 digits identifies it as the decimal separator.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

