                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('TableCrafter rebrand (#1769)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('The plugin is now named TableCrafter. All user-facing labels, headings, and UI copy are updated. Technical identifiers (text domain, Freemius slug, admin menu slug, option keys, shortcodes, PHP prefixes) are unchanged, so no migration is required on existing installs.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.5.0 — Security: server-side role visibility + write gating', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Server-side per-column role visibility (#1763)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Per-column role visibility (Pro #1746) was previously enforced only in the browser, so restricted column values, the visibility map, and your role list still reached the client. Restricted columns are now stripped server-side from both the AJAX entries payload and the rendered table, and the map/roles are no longer sent to the client. Behavior is unchanged; the data simply never leaves the server. Pro-gated; free tier unaffected.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Frontend create + delete are now Pro (#1765)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Creating and deleting entries from the frontend now require Pro, consistent with inline editing, bulk fill, and duplicate. Previously a free site with frontend editing enabled could create and delete real entries. Paying customers are unaffected.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Canonical Plugin URI (#1767)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('The plugin header now points at github.com/TableCrafter/gravity-tables, matching the support/issue links.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.4.9 — Inline Diff Badge + Bulk Fill Preview', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Inline Cell Diff Badge', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('After saving an inline cell edit, a muted "← was: {old value}" badge appears next to the updated cell for 3 seconds then fades out. No Pro requirement — available on all tiers (#1749).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Bulk Fill Diff Preview (Pro)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('While typing a value in the Bulk Fill modal, the Apply button updates live to show "Apply to {N} rows → "{value}"" so the user can confirm scope before committing. Degrades to plain "Apply" on the free tier or when the value field is empty (#1749).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.4.8 — Value-Threshold Email Alerts', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Email Alert Rules (Pro)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Configure threshold-crossing alerts per table in the new "Email Alerts" section of the table builder. Each rule has a field ID, operator (>, <, =, >=, <=, contains), threshold value, and recipient email. An email is sent the first time a field value crosses the threshold after an inline edit, bulk fill, or entry duplicate. Powered by wp_mail(); rules are sanitized and stripped on free tier (#1748).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.4.7 — One-Click Entry Duplicate', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
