                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.4.0 — User Column Visibility Picker', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Column Visibility Picker (Free)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Enable "Column visibility picker" in the table builder Display Options. A "Columns" button appears in the toolbar — visitors toggle columns on or off and their choice is saved per-table to localStorage so the layout survives page reloads. Purely client-side; no extra AJAX requests (#1744).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.3.9 — Configurable Table Auto-Refresh', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Auto-Refresh on Interval (Free)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Set "Auto-refresh interval" in the table builder Display Options. The table silently reloads at the configured interval using the existing loadEntries() path — filters, sort, and pagination are preserved. Minimum interval is 5 seconds; 0 disables. Refresh pauses automatically while a cell is being inline-edited (#1743).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.3.8 — Per-Column Inline Edit Validation Rules', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Per-Column Inline Edit Validation (Pro)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Configure validation rules per column in the field configuration modal: required, min/max character length, min/max numeric value, and a regex pattern with a custom error message. When a cell edit fails a rule, an inline error message blocks the save without interrupting other cells. Pro-gated with persist-strip on save and render-strip in the JS config output (#1742).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.3.7 — Status Badge Cell Type', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Status Badge Cell Type', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Select "Status badge" in the column cell type dropdown, then enter a JSON badge map ({"Pending": {"bg": "#fbbf24", "text": "#000"}}) in the new Badge Map textarea. Matching cell values render as colored pill badges. Non-matching values render as plain text. XSS-safe: all values are esc_html escaped, colors are hex-validated. Works on initial page load and AJAX reloads. Free feature (#1741).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.3.6 — One-Click Table Duplicate', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Table Duplicate', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('A "Duplicate" link now appears in the row actions of every table in the admin list (alongside Edit / Find+Replace / Revisions / Delete). One click clones the full table configuration — form ID, column order, filters, styling, and all Pro settings — into a new table titled "Original Name (Copy)" and takes you straight to its edit page. Free feature (#1740).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v6.3.5 — Data Bars (Pro)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Data Bars', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('New per-column, CSS-only in-cell value bars for numeric columns. In the table builder, turn on the "Show data bar" toggle and pick a color for any numeric column (number / quantity / total / calculation). Each cell renders a horizontal fill BEHIND its number, scaled to the current page maximum, for instant at-a-glance comparison across rows. The number itself is never changed, so the column-totals row, CSV / Excel / PDF export, conditional formatting, and inline editing all keep working exactly as before. Bars are automatically suppressed in card / responsive view, pivot view, server-side-pagination tables, auto-merged (rowspan) columns, and any cell that already has a background color. Pro feature (#1731).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('v4.9.x customer-facing highlights', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <p><?php _e('The v4.9.x audit-thread closed 14 service orphans and shipped these directly customer-facing improvements:', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Bulk migration (Export + Import)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('one-click JSON export of all tables (v4.9.16); upload form with conflict-resolution policy (Skip / Overwrite / Create as new) for round-trip migration (v4.9.17). Useful for staging→production deploys, pre-change backups, cross-site config sharing.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Multi-column sort', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Shift+click adds a secondary tiebreaker (max 3) with numbered badges (1, 2, 3). SQL ORDER BY honors the full stack across pagination (v4.9.0 + v4.9.1).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Per-table layout controls', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Border preset (Classic / Rows only / None / Outer only — v4.9.3), Row height + overflow mode (v4.9.10), Default sort column + direction (v4.9.11), Whole-table collapsible toggle (v4.9.13), Visitor-side length selector "Show N entries" dropdown (v4.9.15).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Filter persistence', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('URL pre-filtering via ?gt_col_X=value (v4.9.6) + per-visitor filter persistence in browser localStorage (v4.9.12). Filters survive page reloads.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Per-column cell types', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Star Rating renderer (numeric → 0–5 SVG stars with role="img" + aria-label, v4.9.7); Per-column totals-row aggregation (Sum / Avg / Min / Max / Count / Count distinct, v4.9.8).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('SEO / accessibility', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Schema.org JSON-LD (Table / Dataset, v4.8.18); RTL completed (v4.9.5). Dataset type drives Google Rich Results.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Print + Export', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Per-table print overrides (paper size / repeat-header / row-striping / excluded columns, v4.9.2); Customizable export filename pattern with token expansion (v4.8.17); PDF button delegates to the real Print flow (v4.8.16, no more deceptive .html download).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('Defensive', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('TC_Data_Integrity_Guard runtime save check (#557, v4.9.14) — aborts with HTTP 409 when the save payload looks destructive (empty title overwriting populated, columns missing when existing had >0). Mirrors the failure mode behind competitor "Lost all my tables" reviews.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong><?php _e('i18n / branding', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></strong> — <?php _e('Customizable pagination labels with {start}/{end}/{total} tokens (v4.8.19 + v4.8.20). Translate or rebrand "Showing X to Y of Z entries" / Previous / Next / "No matching entries" / "Loading…".', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                </ul>

                <h3><?php _e('Recent Versions (v4.32.x – v4.59.x)', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></h3>
                <p class="description"><?php _e('Showing the 5 most recent versions. Use the toggle below to expand the full list.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></p>
                <ul class="gt-recent-versions" data-gt-recent-collapsed="1">
                    <li><strong>6.3.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fix. Advanced filter panel and Filter button were hidden for any table re-saved after the May 9 builder refactor. A missing checkbox meant every save wrote show_advanced_filters: false to the database; the checkbox is restored and a one-time migration resets affected tables.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.3.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fix. The advanced settings panels in the table builder (Pivot view, Server-side pagination, Image fallback and the ones after them) had overlapping, scattered text caused by a missing quote on two tooltips. The panels now lay out cleanly.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.3.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Two UI fixes. Action-column icons (View, Delete, Edit history) now always stay on one row instead of wrapping to a second line in narrow columns. The table builder live preview no longer gets stuck on the loading spinner and renders rows correctly again.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.3.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Smoother loading. Sorting, filtering, or paging a table no longer makes the columns briefly squish together while it reloads, and the loading state now shows shimmer placeholder rows that match the table columns instead of a single Loading flash. Applies to the first load and every reload.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.3.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Performance. A batch of backend optimizations make tables load and render faster on large forms: fewer duplicate lookups, cached date and user-name lookups, a one-time name-field map instead of per-cell scans, smarter shortcode handling, and a cap on filter-dropdown option lists. Plugin assets now load only on pages that actually show a table. No visible changes to how tables look or work.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixes. Choosing "All" in the entries-per-page selector now shows every row instead of just one. Per-table row height, borders, and the loading skeleton apply again, and a repeated WordPress log notice on every table page is gone, after correcting an internal stylesheet-handle name. A debug-only database lookup no longer runs on date-filtered requests.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.8</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Per-column header filters now work: type in a column box to filter by that column, and the Driver and Client columns match by the name shown instead of their internal ID. Every way to export is now in one Export menu (full data as CSV/Excel, or just the visible rows as Copy/CSV/Excel/PDF) with clearer icons and even row heights; the duplicate Export in Bulk Actions has been removed and the toolbar has more breathing room. Tables also load a little faster, and the Freemius SDK was updated to 2.13.2.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Security follow-up to the 6.2.6 review (four fixes). Driver editing is now tied to entry ownership, so a driver can only edit their own rows even on a shared editing-enabled table, with an optional "owner field" setting in the builder to enforce it. Cell contents are cleaned before display, so a value saved into a form can no longer run code in an administrator\'s browser when the table is viewed. The bulk inline-edit action now checks the table\'s allowed-roles list the same way single-row editing already did. And stored integration tokens (Airtable, Notion, cloud, AI) are protected with a stronger encryption key; existing saved tokens keep working and upgrade automatically the next time they are saved. No changes to everyday functionality.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.6</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Security release. A full internal security review hardened every part of the plugin that handles requests, exports, or stored credentials: stricter validation on the data behind tables, the inline edit/delete and bulk actions now confirm you are signed in and acting on the right table, REST endpoints and per-table passwords are enforced consistently, CSV and Excel exports are protected against spreadsheet formula tricks, and stored integration tokens (Airtable, Notion, cloud, AI) are handled more safely. No changes to everyday functionality.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.5</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Hotfix: the new Table History panel (v6.2.3) failed to load its revision list on real sites due to a security-token name mismatch between the browser and the server. Caught in live browser testing the same day; no other features affected.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Search highlighting now covers everything (#1612). Matched text is highlighted in cells that contain links or images, in the mobile card view, and for per-column text filters (each term highlights only within its own column). The highlighter works directly on text nodes, so it can never break a link or land inside HTML markup.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Table history grew up (#1615). The Revisions row action now opens a panel listing your saved snapshots with a change summary for each ("title changed; 2 columns added") instead of asking you to type an index. You can load any snapshot into the builder to review it before saving, or restore it immediately with one click. Also: the Find &amp; Replace column picker now populates for tables saved in the older settings format.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Find &amp; Replace got a proper dialog (#1614). Instead of browser prompts, the tables-list row action now opens a modal where you can scope the replacement to specific columns, toggle case sensitivity or whole-cell matching, and watch a live match count update as you type. The Replace button only unlocks once at least one match has been previewed, so accidental blanket replacements are much harder.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Computed columns round two (#1621). Computed columns are now sortable: clicking the header sorts the rows currently on the page (numbers sort numerically; error cells sink to the bottom). The builder validates formulas as you type them, flagging anything that will not parse before you save. And each computed column can pick a number format: raw, whole numbers with thousands separators, or two decimals. Formats apply in CSV exports too.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.2.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1617): pivot tables can now show several summary columns at once. The builder\'s Pivot view section gained an "Add aggregate" repeater — for example group by Destination and show Rate (Sum), Rate (Avg), and Loads (Count) side by side. Previously only one aggregate could be configured even though the engine and the frontend pivot view already supported several. Existing single-aggregate tables keep working unchanged.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1598): computed columns. In the builder, add read-only columns calculated from your form fields with {field:N} expressions, e.g. {field:3} * {field:5} for quantity times rate, with ROUND / ABS / IF / CONCAT support. Values compute per row when the table loads and are included in CSV exports. Invalid expressions show #ERR in the affected cells. Sorting/filtering on computed columns and inline formula validation are tracked as follow-up work.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.8</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1601): two AI-assist surfaces, both rule-based with no API key required. (1) Table summary line: enable "Show summary line above the table" in the builder and visitors see a one-line digest (row count, date span, numeric min/max/average, dominant values) above the table. (2) Data Quality panel: in the builder, scan any text column for cleanup suggestions (stray whitespace, doubled spaces) and apply fixes per entry with one click — writes go through the same validated path as inline editing.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1605): saved views. The per-user preset dropdown on the frontend toolbar now saves the WHOLE view — filters, column order, sort, and page size — not just filters, and stores it on the user account so it follows logged-in users across devices and browsers. When saving you can mark a preset as your default view (starred in the dropdown); it applies automatically the first time you open the table on a new device, unless URL filters or a remembered local state already apply. Logged-out visitors keep the existing browser-local persistence.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.6</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1596): pivot tables now render on the frontend. Tables with Pivot view enabled (Builder > Pivot view: group-by column + aggregate) previously returned aggregated data that the page could not display — visitors saw mostly-blank rows. The table now shows the pivot layout (one row per group, one column per aggregate such as "Rate (Sum)"), and a toolbar button lets visitors flip between the pivot summary and the raw rows. Pivot rows are read-only. The aggregation engine supports multiple aggregates per group; the builder currently exposes one, with the repeater UI tracked as a follow-up.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.5</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Two transparency fixes. (#1602) The bundle import form now explains that credentials (API keys, Airtable/Notion tokens, webhook URLs, notification emails) are never included in exported bundles, and reminds you to reconfigure integrations after importing on a new site — the scrubbing itself has always happened; now you are told about it. (#1597) The Find & Replace documentation section was rewritten: it previously claimed the feature was not wired up, but the tables-list "Find / Replace" row action with match-count preview has been shipping since the #538 slices.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('New (#1606): search-term highlighting. When a visitor searches a table, the matched text inside each cell is now highlighted, so on wide tables you can see at a glance WHERE the match occurred instead of scanning every column. Works in editable and read-only text cells; case-insensitive; XSS-safe (content is escaped before the highlight wrapper is applied). Theme authors can restyle the highlight color with the --gt-search-hit-bg CSS variable.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Two fixes. (#1608) WordPress 6.9 compatibility: ability registration moved to the dedicated wp_abilities_api_init action. Previously every page load on WP 6.9 emitted six "Function wp_register_ability was called incorrectly" PHP notices and the Gravity Tables abilities (list/query/schema/update/create/delete) were never registered; older WordPress versions keep the previous behavior via an init fallback. (#1603) Renderer consistency: composite-field renderers (address, post image, name) no longer drop a literal 0 value — a 0 zip code, a 0 image URL, or a 0 name prefix/suffix now renders in the cell exactly as it appears in search, filters, and the eye popup.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fix (#1604): the row-link URL safety gate no longer accepts protocol-relative URLs. A template or data value like //evil.example/x starts with a slash, so it rode the site-relative shortcut in TC_Row_Link_Service::is_safe_url() — but browsers resolve that shape to an EXTERNAL site using the current page\'s scheme. The gate now rejects any URL whose first two characters are //, while normal site-relative paths like /loads/7 keep working. Admin-configured row links are unaffected unless they relied on the unsafe shape.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fix (#1595): the Notion / Airtable / JSON push engines and the Notion payload normalizer are now loaded by the plugin. Previously none of the four files were ever required in production, so pushing an edited row back to its external source always failed with "push engine not available" despite the feature shipping since 4.209.0. Pushing edits back to Airtable, Notion, or a custom JSON API now works as documented (tables must opt in with sync_direction push or bidirectional). Also fixes a wall-clock test flake in the date-format relative tests and files #1608 (abilities registry registers on the wrong hook for WordPress 6.9).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.1.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Coverage mega-batch: 47 new PHPUnit test files (+1829 tests / +2630 assertions) drive forty-seven previously-untested classes to ~100% line coverage across two parallel waves — field renderers (time, list, product, creditcard, address, consent, post-image, post-category), filter services (multiselect, cascading, combined, drilldown, find-replace), security guards (path guard, SQL guard, WAF-safe payload, fileupload edit guard, CSV formula detector, inline edit sanitizer, table password, API keys), integration payload builders (Airtable mapper/request builder, Notion normalizer), and platform services (pivot, pagination, sticky rows, toolbar visibility, row link, row expiry, revision snapshots, schema, export filename, bulk migration bundles, asset enqueue gate, AI summarizer/cleanup, save-limit diagnostics, chart refresh, detail rows, URL/request/license/CDN/schema helpers, Divi compat, license cleanup). Suite now 7353 tests / 13400 assertions / 0 errors / 0 failures. Three production findings filed during the audit (#1595 push engines never loaded, #1603 renderer zero-value consistency, #1604 protocol-relative URL gap). No customer-facing behavior changed.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Coverage batch: 9 new PHPUnit test files (+293 tests / +439 assertions) drive nine previously-untested classes to ~100% line coverage — TC_Row_Visibility, TC_SEO_Rows_Renderer, TC_Checkbox_Field_Renderer, TC_Print_Settings_Service, TC_Row_Expiry_Service, TC_Rowspan_Merge_Service, TC_Table_Usage_Indexer, TC_Vertical_Align_Service, TC_Name_Field_Renderer. No production bugs surfaced; all customer-facing behavior unchanged. Pure investment in the test gate so future regressions on these classes are caught at PR time.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.8</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test-quality cleanup (#1592): new tools/test-lint.sh + npm run test:lint statically enforce the conventions documented in tests/TESTING_PRACTICES.md (no empty Throwable catches in tests, no no-op assertTrue(true) without an intent comment, no raw sleep/usleep, no .only/xit/xdescribe, no vague test names, no stray console.log). Lint runs as step 0/4 of the unified runner; suite fails if any sub-suite fails. Cleanup pass narrowed 73 broad Throwable catches to RuntimeException (matching the slice-20 wp_send_json throw seam) and surfaced a hidden test-fixture bug in GTAjaxAirtableAndDeepFillTest (wpdb stub now honors ARRAY_A output mode). 37 bare assertTrue(true) calls now carry an intent comment so the convention is reviewable in git blame. GTDebugTest no longer depends on a 1ms usleep that flaked on fast machines.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Three-tracks-in-one release: (#1590) tools/test-all-suites.sh + npm run test:all runs vitest + phpunit + playwright in sequence. (#1568) PHPUnit suite fully clean: PhpSpreadsheet 2.x setCellValueByColumnAndRow removal worked around (use setCellValue([col,row], val)), risky data provider renamed (testIssueFiles -> issueFilesProvider), edit-field.js setSelectionRange wrapped in try/catch + email type skipped. Suite is now 5231 / 10330 assertions / 0 failures / 0 errors / 0 risky. (#1576) 8 E2E specs expanded from skeletons to real assertions covering table-builder drag-drop, column config modal, CSV/Excel/PDF exports, scheduled exports, charts/pivot, lookup admin. Skip-mode safe.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.6</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Chore (#1577): removed /* c8 ignore file */ blanket markers from 58 JS files. Wave 11 of the 100% coverage push added them to hit literal 100% across the board, but the cost was that any future regression on those files would be invisible to the gate. The surgical /* c8 ignore next */ markers are preserved. Post-cleanup JS coverage: 99.39% statements, 90.09% branches, 97.7% functions -- well above the 95% CI gate threshold from #1574. Future PRs that drop a real branch now fail per-file. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1577-no-c8-ignore-file-markers.test.js.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.5</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Added (#1576): 8 E2E skeleton specs for previously-uncovered admin surfaces (table-builder drag-drop, column-config modal, CSV / Excel / PDF export downloads, scheduled exports, charts and pivot builder, lookup field admin config). Each starts in skip-mode so CI does not need a live WordPress install. Contributors flesh them out incrementally by wiring TC_E2E_BASE_URL to their local instance. Pinned by tests/js/issue-1576-e2e-skeleton-specs-exist.test.js.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Chore (#1575): deleted 5 stale unmerged feature branches (bugfix/eye-popup-measurement-unit, claude/issue-433-keyboard-input, claude/sweet-feynman-VFYoV, feature/backend-gravity-form-integration, feature/improve-ui-editing-experience) that had been sitting unmerged for 4-8 months with content superseded by other work. Total remote branch count now 11 (was 16): main + 10 historical release pointers.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Added (#1574): CI coverage gate at .github/workflows/coverage.yml. Every PR to main and every push to main runs vitest and phpunit with coverage and asserts JS statement coverage and PHP element coverage are both at or above 95%. Below threshold equals build fails. Locks in the 100% achieved in v5.9.4 - v6.0.2. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1574-ci-coverage-gate-workflow.test.js. Vitest 2234/2234.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1567): formula service now evaluates expressions with whitespace between operands. parse_expr and parse_term raw-indexed the next character to detect the operator; when the operand was followed by a space, the while-loop saw the space (not an operator) and broke immediately, returning the left operand alone. "2 + 3" evaluated to 2; only packed forms like "2+3" returned 5. Fix: call skip_whitespace() before sampling the operator in both loops. Regression pinned by tests/GTIssue1567FormulaServiceWhitespaceTest.php.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1566): print header summary preserves zero in number_range / date_range filters. summarizeActiveFilters used f.min || f.max and f.from || f.to as truthy checks. When a user filtered "weight 0 to 10", the 0 was falsy, the disjunction collapsed, and the display fell back to "...". Filters anchored at exactly 0 either rendered as "... to 10" or got silently dropped from the printed header altogether. Fix: explicit !== undefined && !== null && !== "" check so 0 (and the string "0") is preserved. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1566-print-no-falsy-trap-on-zero.test.js. Vitest 2229/2229.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>6.0.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1565): admin field-config modal cannot become un-closable after an internal error. closeModal set self.modalClosing = true before calling closeFieldConfig, but the catch block did not reset the flag. If closeFieldConfig threw, modalClosing stayed true for the rest of the page session and every subsequent close click was short-circuited. The modal became un-closable until a page reload. Fix: added a finally block that resets self.modalClosing = false whether the call succeeds or throws. bump-at-9 leading-digit increment (5.9.9 -> 6.0.0; 5.9.10 illegal). Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1565-bind-events-modalClosing-resets-on-error.test.js. Vitest 2226/2226.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1564): Airtable push-back to source now returns the actual record, not array("raw" => ""). push_row read $response["body"] from TC_Airtable_Sync_Engine::update_record, but the documented return shape is [ok, record, http_code, error] -- no "body" key. Successful pushes silently returned an empty raw-sentinel array; cell-level write to Airtable still worked, only the return value was wrong. Fix: read $response["record"] as documented. Regression pinned by tests/GTIssue1564AirtablePushEngineRecordTest.php. PHPUnit 5222/5222.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.8</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1563): window.gtDebug.dumpTable() no longer throws TypeError. The function was declared with .bind(this) where this was the outer GTDebugFrontend object, but the body called this.getCurrentFilters / this.getCurrentSort -- methods that only exist on the inner window.gtDebug object literal. Every call threw TypeError. Fix: dropped the .bind(this) so this at call time refers to window.gtDebug. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1563-debug-dumpTable-no-typeerror.test.js. Vitest 2224/2224.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1562): saved conditional-formatting color rules now repopulate the picker UI on edit. loadConditionalFormattingRules used $colorInput.next(.gt-rgba-picker-wrapper) to find the picker controls, but initColorPicker appends the wrapper to body (not as a sibling), so the .next() lookup always returned an empty set and the if-body was dead code. Saved color rules rendered with the default #ff0000 in the picker (the cell still painted the actual stored color via the inline value -- only the editor UI was wrong). Fix: initColorPicker now stores the wrapper reference via $input.data(gtColorPickerWrapper); the loader reads it back from the same key. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1562-conditional-format-saved-colors-populate-picker.test.js. Vitest 2221/2221.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.6</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Removed (#1561): orphan date-inputs.js helpers (~80 lines). initializeModalDatePickers and the private convertHtml5DateToFormat declared inside the IIFE in assets/js/frontend/date-inputs.js had no callers anywhere in assets/ or admin/. Pure dead code -- the prototype-attached convertHtml5DateToFormat in util.js (since #841) is what every live consumer uses. Removed cleanly. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1561-date-inputs-no-dead-helpers.test.js. Vitest 2219/2219.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.5</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Removed (#1560): orphan showNotification helper in scroll-indicators.js. The private function declared inside the document-ready block had no callers anywhere in assets/ or admin/ -- pure dead code from a pre-ThickBox era. Removed cleanly. Live notification surfaces are table-utils.js showMessage and edit-history.js toast lifecycle. Regression pinned by tests/js/issue-1560-scroll-indicators-no-dead-showNotification.test.js. Vitest 2216/2216.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1252, #1253, #1254): three bundled tooling fixes. #1253 passes explicit escape backslash to fgetcsv() at the 2 call sites in class-tc-import.php (header read + row loop), silencing the PHP 8.4 deprecation and preserving pre-8.4 backslash-escape semantics; will fatal in PHP 9.0 without this fix. #1252 bumps tests/bootstrap.php memory_limit to 2G to dodge OOM during Clover/HTML coverage serialization. #1254 excludes the built assets/js/frontend-bundle.js and all .config.js files from vitest coverage scope so the built artifact does not deflate the total by approximately 50 points. Shim 3550/7606/0E/0F. Legacy 523/523. Vitest 957/957.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1525, #1538, #1542): three small bugs batched. #1525 adds the class_exists GFAPI false markTestSkipped guard to the unparseable-date test, matching the sibling _missing pattern. #1538 gates the setVal sanitization block in sanitize_conditional_formatting on isset of the action key, preventing a PHP 8 Undefined array key warning when a rule action is rejected by the whitelist (malformed rules are dropped by the required-components check below anyway). #1542 wraps the admin/views/debug-logs.php include in admin_page_debug_logs with a file_exists guard plus a friendly fallback message; the view is optional and did not ship in the plugin tree. Shim 3548/7602/0E/0F -&gt; 3550/7606/0E/0F. Legacy 523/523. Vitest 957/957.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed: pagination, search, length selector, info label, and column filters silently hidden on legacy installs. TC_Toolbar_Visibility_Service::is_visible() returned false for any known component whose key was missing from the supplied settings map. Every install that never saved a toolbar_visibility setting (the opt-in admin UI from #521 slice 2 covers it; most legacy installs do not have it) hit the template gate and silently hid those five toolbar components from the DOM entirely. End users were effectively locked out of every page after the first because the next-page button never rendered. Production report from loadtracker.ajstrucking.com: 3000-entry table showed first 100 rows then no pagination control. Fix: when the component key is missing from settings, fall back to the documented default (visible). Explicit false still hides; explicit true still shows. Matches the class docblock backward-compat promise. 7-AC TDD test in tests/test-issue-toolbar-visibility-missing-key-defaults.php plus local browser verification on the AJS Trucking install &mdash; pagination, search, length selector all back; next button paginates entries 101-200 cleanly. Shim suite 3547/7600/0E/0F -&gt; 3548/7602/0E/0F. Legacy 523/523. Vitest 957/957.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (BUNDLED RELEASE &mdash; 7 TC_Admin sub-slices A-G; slices 106-112; CLOSES the entire 100% coverage push). Second bundled release. 7 test-only PRs (#1536 singleton+menus, #1535 table CRUD readers, #1539 save+sanitizers biggest, #1537 trash+restore, #1541 page renderers, #1534 shortcode migration, #1540 row ordering) authored in parallel by worktree-isolated agents and sequentially squash-merged. Combined delta: +279 tests / +617 assertions. Shim suite 3268/6983/0E/0F -&gt; 3547/7600/0E/0F. Closes the TC_Admin mega-file decomposition (includes/class-tc-admin.php, 1061 statements, was 6.79% baseline -&gt; ~95-100%). HISTORIC MILESTONE: this also CLOSES the entire 100% coverage push -- every file under includes/ is now pinned at ~95-100% line coverage. Two production gaps surfaced: #1538 (sanitize_conditional_formatting unset array key), #1542 (admin_page_debug_logs missing view file). Legacy 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail. Vitest 957/957. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.9.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (BUNDLED RELEASE &mdash; 11 TC_Ajax sub-slices B through L; slices 95-105; CLOSES the TC_Ajax mega-file decomposition). First bundled release in the coverage push. 11 test-only PRs (#1521 filter presets, #1527 find+replace, #1523 audit+history+notifications, #1524 table CRUD, #1529 entry CRUD, #1528 bulk+permissions, #1530 export, #1526 sorting+lookups, #1532 calculations, #1531 migration+WC+Airtable, #1522 transpose+row ops+uploads) were authored in parallel by worktree-isolated agents and then sequentially squash-merged. Combined delta: +489 tests / +1154 assertions. Shim suite 2779/5829/0E/0F -&gt; 3268/6983/0E/0F. Closes the TC_Ajax mega-file decomposition (includes/class-tc-ajax.php, 3611 statements, was 14.71% baseline -&gt; ~95-100%). bump-at-9 leading-digit increment (5.8.10 illegal). Architectural milestone: TC_Ajax was the biggest mega-file in the codebase. Only includes/class-tc-admin.php (1061 statements at 6.79%) remains. Legacy 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail. Vitest 957/957. Patterns codified: every sub-slice agent ran in a worktree-isolated git checkout, used WP_Mock::userFunction exclusively (no parse-time function_exists shims for the prohibited surface), respected setUp baseline_ob_level + tearDown drain, and stopped at PR open without merging. Parent did interim suite checks after merges 1-3 / 1-7 / 1-11 -- all 0E/0F. The parallel-shim discipline held end-to-end. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 94 &mdash; pin TC_Ajax registration + small helpers at ~100%; OPENS the TC_Ajax decomposition). First sub-slice (A) of the includes/class-tc-ajax.php decomposition documented in project_gravity_tables_ajax_decomp_plan &mdash; the biggest mega-file in the codebase (6598 lines / 3611 statements / 14.71% baseline). Pins ~120 statements covering the registration wiring + the small pure helpers that every later sub-slice (B through L, slices 95-105) will reuse. New tests/GTAjaxRegistrationAndHelpersTest.php (84 tests / 109 assertions). Methods covered: get_instance (singleton lifecycle including the null branch); __construct (40+ add_action wirings across admin AJAX endpoints, frontend AJAX endpoints with nopriv counterparts, filter presets admin-only, find-and-replace admin-only, push-row admin-only, and the ob_start output-buffer initialization that prevents stray output from corrupting JSON responses per #113); gt_clean_output_buffers (drain-all-buffers contract verified by stacking three extra buffers on top of the constructors and asserting the drain reaches zero, plus the no-op-when-empty branch); safe_log (silent-when-logger-null guard, level-method dispatch via an anonymous capturing logger, exception swallowing when the logger throws); gt_assert_save_integrity (missing-table_id null short-circuit, table_id-zero null short-circuit, no-existing-row null short-circuit, clean-save passes, empty-title-overwriting-populated returns the integrity_empty_title_overwrites_populated envelope, empty-columns-overwriting-populated returns the integrity_empty_columns_overwrites_populated envelope, non-string-settings json_decode skip); invalidate_table_caches (three group flushes in order gravity_tables / gravity_forms / gf_entries, GFCache flush invocation when the class exists, gf_clear_entry_cache only when an entry_id is supplied &mdash; not on null/omitted); count_wp_placeholders (counts