h_group and gf_clear_entry_cache (invalidate_table_caches observation seams) so the shims stay method-scoped and do not bleed across files via Patchwork. In-file function_exists-guarded shims for sanitize_text_field / sanitize_textarea_field / sanitize_email / esc_url_raw / wp_kses because bootstrap does not pre-declare them (tests/helpers/stubs.php declares them but is only loaded by the legacy custom runner). GFCache stub installed at file top with a class_exists guard and a flush_count static counter for observation. gt_assert_save_integrity exercised through the slice 21 SQL-pattern fixture seam (GLOBALS gt_test_wpdb_fixtures get_row) so the SELECT title, settings FROM wpdb prepare round-trip can be staged per-test without a full Mockery wpdb instance. TC_Inline_Edit_Sanitizer and TC_Sanitization_Service are the real production classes (autoloaded by tablecrafter.php before class-tc-ajax.php), so the class_exists branches in sanitize_field_value route through real production logic and the assertions pin the contract end-to-end. PHPUnit risky-test-did-not-close-its-own-output-buffers guard is sidestepped by recording the baseline ob_get_level in setUp and draining back to baseline in tearDown &mdash; the constructor opens one buffer (#113) so every test that touches the singleton would otherwise leak. The two tests that explicitly drain buffers re-open buffers up to baseline before returning so PHPUnit own output capture continues to work for sibling tests in the same process. Patterns reused: slice 56 (GTShortcodeRegisterScriptsTest &mdash; sub-slice A of the TC_Shortcode decomp, the same registration + helpers template); slice 93 (GTLookupTest &mdash; WP_Mock userFunction discipline + private method access via ReflectionMethod invokeArgs); slice 21 (wpdb SQL-pattern fixture seam); slice 28 (GTAdminLoggerSeamTest &mdash; GFCache stub + singleton override seam contract). Shim suite: 2695 tests / 5720 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky -&gt; 2779 tests / 5829 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (+84 / +109). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). Coverage delta: ~120 statements of includes/class-tc-ajax.php (registration wiring + the listed small helpers) pinned at ~100%. The remaining ~3490 statements ship across sub-slices B through L (slices 95-105, v5.9.0 -&gt; v6.0.0 under the bump-at-9 rule). This slice OPENS the TC_Ajax decomposition &mdash; the biggest mega-file in the codebase, the second-to-last decomp target before TC_Admin closes out the 100% campaign. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.8</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 93 &mdash; pin TC_Lookup to ~100%; CLOSES the partial-fill campaign). Last partial-fill slice. Targets includes/class-tc-lookup.php (294 statements) from a 1.36% baseline to ~100% lines / ~100% methods. Every non-mega-file production class is now pinned &mdash; only the TC_Ajax (3611 statements at 14.71%) and TC_Admin (1061 statements at 6.79%) mega-file decompositions remain. New tests/GTLookupTest.php (76 tests / 113 assertions). TC_Lookup is the singleton value-transformation layer used by TC_Entry_Repository (slice 92) and the shortcode display path. It resolves three lookup types: user (returns one of six profile fields display_name, user_login, user_email, first_name, last_name, user_nicename); post (returns one of four post fields post_title, post_excerpt, post_status, post_type); custom-table (looks up a row in any allowlisted custom table via TC_SQL_Guard is_safe_identifier). Provides single-value (process_lookup_value) and batched (process_lookup_values_batch) transforms plus dropdown-source generation (get_lookup_options) that intersects the configured source with the actual values referenced in a given Gravity Forms form via the wp_gf_entry / wp_gf_entry_meta join. Coverage targets every branch: singleton lifecycle (get_instance null-branch and identity, class-shape contract); process_lookup_value guard branches (empty-value, empty-config, missing-type, unknown-type) and dispatch to lookup_user, lookup_post, lookup_custom; lookup_user (falsy-id early return, user-not-found, all six user_field branches including first_name and last_name via get_user_meta, unknown-field fallback to display_name); lookup_post (falsy-id early return, post-not-found, all four post_field branches, unknown-field fallback to post_title); lookup_custom (table / id_column / display_column empty branches; inline preg_match reject paths for unsafe identifiers; wpdb get_var hit returns the display value, miss returns the original id); process_lookup_values_batch (same guard branches plus type dispatch); lookup_users_batch (intval-filter early-return when nothing survives, all six user-field branches plus unknown-field fallback); lookup_posts_batch (intval-filter early-return, all four post-field branches plus unknown-field fallback); lookup_custom_batch (column-empty guards, three TC_SQL_Guard reject paths for unsafe identifiers, happy-path result mapping keyed by id); get_lookup_options (type guards plus dispatch); get_user_options (no-form-id fallback with number 100 cap, form-id used-ids intersect via gf_entry / gf_entry_meta join, user_roles and lookup_user_roles config aliases both fire role__in, all six label-field branches plus unknown-field fallback, empty-label skip via the not-empty label guard); get_post_options (no-form-id fallback, form-id used-ids intersect, all four label-field branches plus unknown-field fallback, empty-label skip, custom post_type config); get_custom_options (column-empty guards, three TC_SQL_Guard reject paths, no-form-id raw SELECT LIMIT 100 fallback, form-id used-values intersect via wp_gf_entry_meta, empty-used-values short-circuit that skips the custom-table SELECT entirely). Private methods reached via Reflection. Strategy: real TC_Lookup singleton (reset between tests via reflection &mdash; PHP 8.5 setAccessible(true) deprecation avoided per suite lesson 4; no-op since PHP 8.1) under a Mockery-mocked wpdb (slice 92 pattern) for the get_options paths that hit the gf_entry / gf_entry_meta joins and the custom-table SELECT. WP_Mock userFunction for every WP surface (get_user_by, get_users, get_user_meta, get_post, get_posts, sanitize_text_field) &mdash; bootstrap does not declare them so WP_Mock owns them cleanly without parse-time races. Real TC_SQL_Guard is_safe_identifier for the centralised allowlist branches. Test fixture stores keyed by id so per-test setup is one-line. Patterns reused: slice 92 (GTEntryRepositoryTest) Mockery-mocked wpdb typehint placeholder plus singleton-reset via reflection; slice 91 (GTDebugTest) WP_Mock userFunction discipline; slice 90 (GTConfigurationServiceTest) get_option / update_option parse-time race avoidance; slice 76 (GTSqlGuardTest) real TC_SQL_Guard is_safe_identifier. Shim suite: 2619 tests / 5607 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky -&gt; 2695 tests / 5720 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (+76 / +113). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). Coverage delta: includes/class-tc-lookup.php from 1.36% -&gt; ~100% lines / ~100% methods. This slice closes the partial-fill campaign &mdash; only the TC_Ajax and TC_Admin mega-file decompositions remain. The per-file fill template has now been applied across the entire non-mega-file production surface. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 92 &mdash; pin TC_Entry_Repository to 100%; FIFTH and FINAL slice of batch 12, partial-coverage catch-up). Replaces the stub tests/GTEntryRepositoryTest.php (1 test / 1 assertion) with a comprehensive 74-test / 113-assertion file covering includes/repositories/class-tc-entry-repository.php (283 statements) from a 2.83% baseline to 100% lines / 100% methods. TC_Entry_Repository is the data-access layer behind TC_Entry_Service (slice 63); it wraps three collaborators (TC_Query_Builder, TC_Lookup singleton, TC_Configuration_Service) and encapsulates every $wpdb query against wp_gf_entry / wp_gf_entry_meta that the entry-display layer needs. Coverage targets every branch: findById hit and miss; findByIds empty-input early-return, intval coercion, null-result fallback; getEntryMeta keyed-map happy path with field_ids filter; updateEntryMeta success, multi-field, returns-false-no-error, throws TC_Database_Exception when wpdb-last_error is set; bulkUpdate counts payload with empty entry_ids and partial-failures; bulkDelete success counts with intval coercion and exception when last_error is set; canUserEditEntry admin short-circuit via user_can edit_posts, meta-exists path, no-meta path; getForExport GFAPI-missing class_exists branch (process-isolated), form-missing early-return, happy-path with form and entries payload (all three branches under process isolation); getUniqueValues DISTINCT query against gf_entry_meta; getValueCountsAndFirstSeen typed-payload mapping (value, count, first_seen) and non-array null fallback; getUniqueValuesMatching no-search, with-search LIKE clause, limit clamp low to 1, limit clamp high to 200, non-array null fallback; countByFormId defaults and every filter shape; findByFormId default payload, processes rows and computes total_pages, applies pagination offset, all-filter combinations, custom-filter switch arms for text, dropdown, lookup, checkboxes, date_range, number_range plus default-arm and skip arms for non-array filters and missing-type guards. Private helpers reached via Reflection: applyCustomFilters every branch including all skip guards; applyDateRangeFilter from-only, to-only, both; applyNumberRangeFilter min-only, max-only, both, non-numeric skip; applySorting entry_id branch, date_created branch, numeric-type CAST branch, text-type plain orderBy branch, lookup routing branch, fallback-to-date_created arm; applyLookupSorting orderBy fallback; processEntryResults empty-rows, dotted field id alias path (4.1 maps to field_4_1), missing-field falls back to empty string, lookup-processor invocation arm; formatDateDisplay empty-input, midnight-uses-date-format, time-set-uses-datetime-format, unparseable-returns-raw; normalizeDateFormat empty-input, zero-pads single-digit MM/DD, passes-through non-three-parts, already-padded preserved. Strategy: real TC_Query_Builder + TC_Configuration_Service + TC_Lookup under a Mockery-mocked $wpdb so the SQL paths execute end-to-end and only the final wpdb call returns fixture data. TC_Database_Exception::fromWpdb has a wpdb typehint &mdash; we declare a structural placeholder class wpdb at file top (mirrors GTExceptionsTest slice 27) and build mocks via Mockery::mock(wpdb::class) so they satisfy instanceof wpdb. WP_Mock::userFunction for every WP function (current_time, user_can, get_option, update_option) &mdash; post-slice-91 lesson: parse-time function_exists shims bleed across files; Patchwork-rewritten WP_Mock interceptions stay method-scoped. getForExport branches exercised under PHPUnit process isolation with Mockery::mock(alias:GFAPI) (slice 40 GTMergedTableTest pattern); the GFAPI-missing branch requires process isolation because sibling tests alias declarations leak. TC_Lookup singleton reset between tests via reflection; PHP 8.5 setAccessible(true) deprecation avoided per suite lesson 4 &mdash; the call is a no-op since PHP 8.1. Patterns reused: slice 63 (GTEntryServiceTest) Mockery-wpdb and TC_Lookup-singleton-reset template; slice 27 (GTExceptionsTest) structural wpdb stub; slice 40 (GTMergedTableTest) GFAPI alias mocking; slice 90 (GTConfigurationServiceTest) WP_Mock get_option / update_option; slice 91 (GTDebugTest) WP_Mock for ALL WP surface to keep shims method-scoped. Shim suite: 2546 tests / 5495 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky -&gt; 2619 tests / 5607 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (+73 / +112). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). Coverage delta: includes/repositories/class-tc-entry-repository.php from 2.83% -&gt; 100% lines / 100% methods. This slice CLOSES batch 12 (slices 88-92, v5.8.3 -&gt; v5.8.7) &mdash; the partial-coverage catch-up batch landed in five sequential releases: TC_AI_Ajax (~100% via slice 88), TC_Clipboard_Paste_Handler (97.73% lines via slice 89), TC_Configuration_Service (~100% via slice 90), TC_Debug (~100% via slice 91), TC_Entry_Repository (100% via slice 92). Total batch delta: +253 tests / +542 assertions across 5 production files moved from a weighted-average ~14% baseline to ~100%. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.6</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 91 &mdash; pin TC_Debug to ~100%; FOURTH slice of batch 12, partial-coverage catch-up). New tests/GTDebugTest.php (60 tests / 127 assertions) pins includes/class-tc-debug.php (245 statements) from 7.76% to ~100%. Strategy: WP_Mock::userFunction for ALL WP surface (post-slice-90 lesson &mdash; Patchwork wins over parse-time function_exists shims and keeps interception method-scoped). The two parse-time shims that remain (current_user_can / get_current_user_id) read from the post-#1206 globals (_gt_test_user_caps / _gt_test_current_user_id) so they do not shadow alphabetically-later test files. Shim suite: 2486 tests / 5368 assertions / 0E / 0F -&gt; 2546 tests / 5495 assertions / 0E / 0F (+60 / +127). Legacy 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail. Vitest 957/957. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.5</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 90 &mdash; pin TC_Configuration_Service to ~100%; THIRD slice of batch 12, partial-coverage catch-up). Third slice of batch 12 &mdash; the partial-coverage catch-up batch that picks up files left between 0% and 100% by the prior 0%-file campaign. Targets includes/services/class-tc-configuration-service.php (122 statements) from a 19.67% baseline to ~100%. New tests/GTConfigurationServiceTest.php (66 tests / 112 assertions). TC_Configuration_Service is the centralised plugin-settings container &mdash; a pure-PHP class with a handful of WordPress integration points (get_option / update_option for persistence, __() for the one i18n error string in validateConfiguration). It exposes static constants for default per-page (25), min and max per-page (1 and 100), default date and datetime formats, and three field-type allowlists (non-editable IDs like id / date_created / date_updated; filterable types; sortable types). The constructor merges a caller-supplied overrides array over getDefaultSettings so arbitrary extra keys flow through unchanged. get is a null-coalesce read with a caller-supplied default; set is a direct write. getPerPage clamps the merged per_page setting to the MIN_PER_PAGE / MAX_PER_PAGE range after an int cast, so a stored string 17 becomes int 17, a stored 0 floors to 1, and a stored 9999 ceilings to 100. getDateFormat and getDateTimeFormat round-trip with the defaults. isFieldEditable with a non-empty field id short-circuits to false when the field id is in the non-editable list (so a text field with id date_created is still blocked from edit), otherwise reads the field-type list; an empty field id falls through cleanly to the type check. isFieldFilterable and isFieldSortable are pure list lookups &mdash; the test pins their differences (textarea is filterable but NOT sortable; hidden is filterable; signature is neither). getAllowedBulkActions returns the merged setting (defaults to delete and export); getCacheDuration floors negatives to zero after an int cast; getMaxEntriesPerRequest floors to one. isDebugLoggingEnabled returns the explicit opt-in enable_debug_logging OR the WP_DEBUG constant truth &mdash; the explicit-true branch is asserted directly, the WP_DEBUG branch is verified to match defined(WP_DEBUG) AND WP_DEBUG so the test is parse-order-independent. getFieldDefaults walks a switch over field type and returns per-type filter_config shapes: date returns type date, date_range single, show_presets true; number and phone share type range, range_step 1, range_format number; select and radio share type dropdown, multiple false, sort_options alphabetical; multiselect and checkbox share type checkboxes, checkboxes_logic or, show_select_all true; everything else falls through the default arm to type text, case_sensitive false, exact_match false. Each switch case has a dedicated test, plus a non-editable-field case (source_url) that pins all three booleans (editable, filterable, sortable) to false on the same return shape. createTableConfiguration is instance-checked against TC_Table_Configuration and verified to layer overrides over the merged settings (a service-level per_page plus a call-time form_id override both survive into the configuration object). validateConfiguration is the only public method that can throw &mdash; the test exercises every path: per-page in range (50 passes), per-page below MIN_PER_PAGE (0 throws TC_Validation_Exception), per-page above MAX_PER_PAGE (9999 throws), boolean coercion (string true, integer 1, boolean false round-trip through TC_Sanitization_Service sanitizeBoolean correctly), bulk-actions intersection with the delete / export / edit allowlist (hack_action filtered out, the three allowed values preserved), non-array bulk_actions falls through and the default carries through, an unrelated custom_key in the existing settings survives the merge, and an empty config returns the defaults without raising. toArray returns the full settings map (asserted for an overridden key plus two structural-key existence checks). loadFromOptions and saveToOptions are tested in three shapes: (1) loadFromOptions merges a previously-saved array over the defaults; (2) when the stored option is a non-array (e.g. string corrupted), the is_array guard skips the merge and the defaults remain untouched; (3) when no option is stored at all, the call is a no-op. saveToOptions writes and returns true on success; the test also forces update_option to return false and asserts the method propagates that. A round-trip test save-and-reload through a fresh service confirms the option key is gravity_tables_settings end-to-end. Strategy: WP_Mock-backed get_option and update_option shims sidestep the function-declaration race against sibling tests (GTAutoloadManagerTest, GTTemplateServiceTest, GTEntryServiceTest, test-issue-505-api-key-service.php, and others) that each declare their own under function_exists guards &mdash; whichever file loads first under the PHPUnit directory scan wins the global namespace, and Patchwork cannot intercept once a real PHP function exists. WP_Mock Patchwork-backed userFunction declaration always wins regardless of declaration order. __ and sanitize_text_field shimmed at file top under function_exists guards (slice-41 pattern) so the dependency chain (TC_Validation_Service, TC_Sanitization_Service, TC_Validation_Exception, TC_Table_Configuration) parses cleanly. No wpdb, no GFAPI, no process isolation needed. Patterns reused: slice 41 GTConfigPortServiceTest (sibling service-class layout + function_exists-guarded shims at file top); slice 63 GTEntryServiceTest (comprehensive service-class template); slice 89 GTClipboardPasteHandlerTest (WP_Mock userFunction for option-store overrides). Shim suite: 2420 tests / 5256 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky -&gt; 2486 tests / 5368 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (+66 / +112). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). Coverage delta: includes/services/class-tc-configuration-service.php from 19.67% -&gt; ~100%. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 89 &mdash; pin TC_Clipboard_Paste_Handler to ~100%; SECOND slice of batch 12, partial-coverage catch-up). Second slice of batch 12 &mdash; the partial-coverage catch-up batch that picks up files left between 0% and 100% by the prior 0%-file campaign. Targets includes/services/class-tc-clipboard-paste-handler.php (89 statements) from a 14.61% baseline to ~100% line coverage (97.73% &mdash; 86/88 lines; the two not-covered lines are defensive 500 guards on class_exists(TC_TSV_Parser_Service) and class_exists(TC_Admin) and class_exists(GFAPI) whose false arm cannot fire under the shim because tests/bootstrap.php pre-loads all three classes &mdash; pinned via source-shape guards instead). New tests/GTClipboardPasteHandlerTest.php (39 tests / 146 assertions). TC_Clipboard_Paste_Handler is the admin-side AJAX surface behind the issue #516 paste-from-Excel-Sheets-Numbers affordance. It registers two wp_ajax_* hooks: wp_ajax_gt_clipboard_paste_preview (parse a clipboard payload via TC_TSV_Parser_Service, return dialect + row count + a 5-row preview &mdash; no DB writes) and wp_ajax_gt_clipboard_paste_apply (parse the payload, optionally trash existing entries when mode equals replace, then create one Gravity Forms entry per parsed row via GFAPI add_entry). It also exposes the pure helper rewire_columns_by_header which case-insensitively maps a parsed header row to the table saved column ids, falling back to null on partial / empty / no-match so the apply path can safely revert to positional mapping. Coverage targets every branch: boot() registers both AJAX actions and pairs them with ajax_preview / ajax_apply exactly (class-shape Reflection contract pinned for all three public static methods as : void with zero parameters); ajax_preview 403 when manage_options denied; ajax_preview 400 when POST tsv is empty AND when the tsv key is absent (covers the isset ternary false arm); ajax_preview 200 happy path with dialect detection (tsv when tabs present, csv when only commas), rows and cols count round-trip, and the 5-row preview cap honoured even when the input is 10+ rows; wp_unslash flow verified by feeding magic-quotes-style backslash-escaped quotes and asserting the unescaped string lands in the preview. ajax_apply 403 when manage_options denied; 400 when table_id is missing, 0, or tsv is empty; 404 when the TC_Admin override returns null for the requested table_id; 400 when the row exists but form_id is 0 (table not bound to a GF); invalid mode values coerced to append; missing mode defaults to append. Append happy path asserts GFAPI add_entry is called once per parsed row with the GF entry payload shape (form_id + column-id-keyed cell values). Replace happy path asserts GFAPI get_entries is called with the canonical status active filter + offset 0 page_size 5000 paging, then GFAPI update_entry status trash plus id once per existing entry, then add_entry once per new row &mdash; with the is_array existing guard exercised separately by returning a WP_Error from get_entries (deleted stays at 0, added still proceeds), and the not-empty entry id skip exercised by feeding rows of id 0, no id, and id 99 then asserting only entry 99 is trashed. Header rewire happy path: has_headers 1 with column_labels 3 Driver 5 Status and headers Status Driver reverses the column ids to 5 3 so the captured add_entry payload routes complete to field 5, Bob to field 3 rather than the positional complete to field 3, Bob to field 5 mis-mapping. Partial match falls back to positional (Driver Unknown &mdash; rewire returns null so effective_columns stays at the saved positional order). Missing column_labels config falls through the same null-rewire path. add_entry WP_Error return: counted into the errors total without breaking the loop (asserts added 1 errors 1 for a 2-row paste where the first add_entry returns WP_Error). No-saved-columns config: effective_columns or null flips to null, to_rows uses the first parsed row as header keys, the GF entry payload is keyed by the parsed header strings rather than numeric column ids. rewire_columns_by_header contract pinned (6 tests): null on empty headers; full match reorders; case-insensitivity + whitespace trim; partial match returns null; empty-trimmed header cell aborts; column without a saved label is excluded from the index. Source-shape guards: no wp_remote_*, no curl_exec, no HTTP file_get_contents, the canonical gt_clipboard_paste nonce action literal is present, both AJAX handlers gate on current_user_can manage_options (counted via substr_count so a future drop of either gate flags here), the is_scalar val and string val casts in the row-map to entry loop are present. Strategy: uses the slice-20 wp_send_json_* throw seam (GLOBALS gt_test_send_json_throws equals true) so each handler short-circuits and the test inspects the captured payload from GLOBALS gt_test_response. WP_Mock userFunction overrides for current_user_can / __ / wp_unslash are installed in setUp &mdash; the PHPUnit suite does not load tests/helpers/stubs.php, so without these overrides Patchwork has no real declaration to race against and the production reads see undefined-function fatals. The slice-28 GLOBALS gt_test_admin_override seam plugs in an anonymous-class fake TC_Admin exposing only the two methods the handler reads (get_table id, get_table_config id) so each test can configure the fixture row + config in one line. Mockery::mock alias:GFAPI with per-test shouldReceive expectations covers the add_entry / get_entries / update_entry calls &mdash; same pattern as slice 40 (GTMergedTableTest), slice 48 (GTWooCommerceTest). No wpdb, no process isolation needed since the dependency-not-loaded 500 guards are unreachable under the shim. Patterns reused: legacy tests/test-issue-516-slice2-clipboard-paste.php and tests/test-issue-516-slice3-header-match.php (source-shape + rewire contract); slice 88 GTAiAjaxTest (throw-seam + Reflection contract pinning template); slice 40 GTMergedTableTest (TC_Admin override + GFAPI alias); slice 47 GTExternalDBTest (AJAX-style handler test layout). Shim suite: 2381 tests / 5110 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky -&gt; 2420 tests / 5256 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (+39 / +146). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). Coverage delta: includes/services/class-tc-clipboard-paste-handler.php from 14.61% -&gt; 97.73% lines. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 88 &mdash; pin TC_AI_Ajax to ~100%; FIRST slice of batch 12, partial-coverage catch-up). First slice of batch 12 &mdash; the partial-coverage catch-up batch that picks up files left between 0% and 100% by the prior 0%-file campaign. Targets includes/services/ai/class-tc-ai-ajax.php (26 statements) from a 19.23% baseline to ~100%. New tests/GTAiAjaxTest.php (15 tests / 44 assertions). TC_AI_Ajax is the AJAX surface for the AI column-type detector &mdash; it exposes a single hook (wp_ajax_gt_ai_detect_column_types) routed at TC_AI_Ajax handle_detect_column_types, which gates on nonce + manage_options capability + non-zero form_id, then delegates to TC_AI_Column_Type_Detector detect and serialises the result via wp_send_json_success or wp_send_json_error. Coverage targets every branch: invalid-nonce 403 path; missing-nonce-request-param 403 path; insufficient-capability 403 path; missing-form_id 400 path; form_id = 0 400 path; detector returning WP_Error 400 path with code + message round-tripped through the response payload; sample_size = abc -&gt; absint -&gt; 0 -&gt; falsy -&gt; fallback to 25 (still hits the no-provider WP_Error arm so the absint coercion is exercised without needing an HTTP stub); explicit sample_size = 50 flowing through unchanged. register() action wiring is covered too &mdash; the test clears the bootstrap add_action capture array, calls register, then asserts the wp_ajax_gt_ai_detect_column_types hook holds the TC_AI_Ajax handle_detect_column_types callable pair exactly. Class-shape guards pin register and handle_detect_column_types as public static : void with zero parameters via Reflection, plus source-level invariants (no wp_remote_*, no curl_exec, no HTTP file_get_contents, references the detector class, uses the canonical nonce action). Uses the slice-20 wp_send_json_* throw seam (GLOBALS gt_test_send_json_throws = true) so the handler short-circuits and