                    <li><strong>5.8.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1206): repair PHPUnit shim suite &mdash; 14E/5F -&gt; 0E/0F (test-infra only). The PHPUnit shim suite (vendor/bin/phpunit) had 14 errors + 5 failures on main that were invisible to tools/test-all.sh and tools/build-release.sh. All in two files: tests/GTImportTest.php (14E + 4F) and tests/GTExceptionsTest.php (1F). Root cause: two compounding parse-time function-symbol races. (1) tests/GTShortcodeExternalSourceTest.php declares set_transient at file-parse time. PHPUnit directory scan loads every Test.php file before tests run, so its global shim wins the function-symbol race against GTImportTest WP_Mock userFunction closure (Patchwork cannot intercept once a real PHP function exists). The global shim wrote raw values to GLOBALS _gt_test_transients while GTImportTest read from a separate this transients property under a value plus ttl wrapper, so assertions saw an empty array on every transient read. (2) tests/GTErrorHandlerTest.php declares get_current_user_id returning literal 7 at parse time. Same race fires here: under the full suite the production code keyed transients as gt_import_result_7 while GTImportTest assertions looked for gt_import_result_1, AND the GTExceptionsTest permission-exception fallback test assertSame 0 saw 7 instead. Fix shape (smallest viable, test-only): bind this transients by reference to GLOBALS _gt_test_transients and drop the wrapper schema so both shim paths converge on the same backing store; make GTErrorHandlerTest get_current_user_id runtime-overridable via GLOBALS _gt_test_current_user_id with default 7 fallback so GTImportTest setUp value of 1 takes effect without losing the file existing assertSame 7 regression guard; rewrite the GTExceptionsTest fallback test to drive GLOBALS _gt_test_current_user_id to 0 in a try-finally and assert getUserId equals get_current_user_id so the test is order-independent. No production code touched (proven by isolating each failure: the test files passed when run standalone via vendor/bin/phpunit tests/GTImportTest.php, only failing under the full directory scan). Shim suite delta: 2366 tests / 5038 assertions / 14E / 5F / 11 skipped -&gt; 2366 tests / 5066 assertions / 0E / 0F / 13 skipped / 1 risky (the risky is the pre-existing PHPUnitShimTest testIssueFiles no-assertion guard, untouched by this PR). GTErrorHandlerTest unaffected (still 39 tests / 85 assertions). Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0 (523 files green, 64 vitest files / 957 vitest tests green). No customer-facing runtime change &mdash; this is test infrastructure repair so future PR regressions in modern test files surface against the release gate.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Fixed (#1197): TC_Table_Builder::validate_config TypeError on every call. The method declared : bool but unconditionally returned the errors array. PHP threw TypeError on every invocation, including the empty-error happy path. Fix: change return type to : array to match existing semantics. Callers check empty(errors) or iterate. Surfaced by slice 65 coverage push; closed here. Three slice-65 tests flipped from expectException(TypeError) to asserting the actual array shape: empty config returns 3 missing-field errors, missing form returns 1 does not exist error, valid config returns empty array. Shim 14E/5F unchanged (#1206 pre-existing). Legacy 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail. Vitest 957/957.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.8.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 87 &mdash; pin TC_AI_Provider interface at ~100%; CLOSES batch 11 + CLOSES the 0%-file campaign). Fifth and final slice of batch 11 &mdash; and the final slice in the 0%-file campaign across batches 7-11 (slices 63-87, v5.5.6 -&gt; v5.8.0). After this lands, every 0% file in includes/ is pinned at ~100% line coverage. New tests/GTAiProviderInterfaceTest.php (13 tests / 26 assertions) pins includes/services/ai/interface-gt-ai-provider.php (2 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100%. TC_AI_Provider is the single seam every AI feature talks to &mdash; feature code resolves a provider via TC_AI_Provider_Registry::active() and calls complete() against the interface, never against a vendor SDK directly. The interface declares four methods: is_configured returning bool, provider_id returning string, label returning string, and complete taking a string prompt plus an optional array options parameter and returning either a string or a WP_Error. The interface declaration itself does not contribute executable statements; the only line PHPUnit can attribute coverage to is the if not defined ABSPATH guard. Defining ABSPATH before requiring the file pins it at ~100%. Strategy: Reflection-based contract test pins the four public method names via a sorted-array assert; return types pinned for is_configured returns bool, provider_id returns string, label returns string; complete parameter shape pinned (required string prompt, optional array options with default empty array); complete return type is intentionally undeclared because the union string-or-WP_Error is a PHP-8.0 union type that the supported PHP-7.x install base cannot parse &mdash; pinned via getReturnType equals null so a future PR that adds a stricter return type without coordinating callers surfaces here. Three concrete stub providers (TC_AI_Provider_OpenAI, TC_AI_Provider_Anthropic, TC_AI_Provider_Gemini) are each asserted to implement the interface via class_implements AND instantiate as a valid TC_AI_Provider &mdash; the exact contract TC_AI_Provider_Registry::active relies on at its return point (the registry resolves a class name from a settings map and constructs it, then narrows the return type via instanceof TC_AI_Provider). Any future PR that strips an implements clause from a concrete provider or renames a method on the interface breaks the test before it can break the registry. No wpdb, no GFAPI, no hook registration, no process isolation, no inline-style enqueue. ABSPATH is defined-guarded so a future process-isolated test does not surface an undefined-constant warning when this file is the first one to load. Patterns reused: slice 27 (GTExceptionsTest &mdash; interface / abstract contract pinning via Reflection); slice 86 (GTRtlServiceTest &mdash; concise per-slice service test template). Shim suite: 2353 tests / 5012 assertions -&gt; 2366 tests / 5038 assertions (+13 / +26). Pre-existing 14E/5F count (per #1206) is unchanged. Legacy tools/test-all.sh: EXIT=0. Vitest: 64 files / 957 tests &mdash; unchanged. Coverage delta: includes/services/ai/interface-gt-ai-provider.php from 0% -&gt; ~100%. Batch 11 close-out (slices 83-87, v5.7.6 -&gt; v5.8.0): all five files in this batch (TC_Excel_Float_Service, TC_Accessibility_Service, TC_Fuzzy_Search_Service, TC_RTL_Service, TC_AI_Provider interface) now sit at ~100% line coverage. 0%-file campaign close-out (batches 7-11, slices 63-87, v5.5.6 -&gt; v5.8.0): every originally-0% file in includes/ is now pinned. bump-at-9 leading-digit increment exercised at v5.8.0 (5.7.9 + 1 patch would have been the illegal 5.7.10, so the leading digit ticks). No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.7.9</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 86 &mdash; pin TC_RTL_Service at ~100%). Fourth slice of batch 11 &mdash; the final 0% batch in the 100% coverage push. New tests/GTRtlServiceTest.php (9 tests / 9 assertions / 1 skipped) pins includes/services/class-tc-rtl-service.php (13 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line + method coverage. TC_RTL_Service is the thin right-to-left language presenter that exposes four static helpers consumed by the shortcode renderer and the asset enqueue pipeline. Four public static methods, all exercised. is_rtl() covered &mdash; delegates to the WP global is_rtl() under a function_exists guard so the service stays safe to call before the WP locale stack is fully wired (pinned by flipping a controllable GLOBALS _gt_test_is_rtl flag and asserting both the LTR (false) and RTL (true) return values). get_dir_attr() covered &mdash; pure ternary over is_rtl() emitting either dir=rtl (RTL languages like Arabic, Hebrew, Persian) or dir=ltr (every other locale) for the wrapper div that hosts the table; both arms asserted with literal-string equality so any change to the attribute shape (e.g. dropping quotes, swapping single-quotes) is flagged. get_wrapper_classes() covered &mdash; pure ternary over is_rtl() emitting either gt-rtl or gt-ltr for the wrapper element so theme CSS can target the directional variant without re-querying body[dir] (both arms asserted). enqueue_rtl_styles() covered &mdash; short-circuit branch verified when is_rtl() returns false (no wp_enqueue_style call recorded against our handle, and the structured-capture key stays empty); passthrough branch verified when is_rtl() returns true (the gt-frontend-rtl handle is registered, the dependency is gravity-tables-frontend &mdash; matching the post-v4.8.14 handle from class-tc-shortcode.php register_assets so the legacy gt-frontend mismatch noted in the inline comment can never regress, the cache buster is TC_VERSION, and the src path 