                    <li><strong>5.7.7</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 84 &mdash; pin TC_Accessibility_Service at ~100%). Second slice of batch 11 &mdash; the final 0% batch in the 100% coverage push. New tests/GTAccessibilityServiceTest.php (17 tests / 32 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-accessibility-service.php (25 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line + method coverage. TC_Accessibility_Service is the WCAG 2.1 AA presenter + enqueue helper that injects ARIA attributes, visually-hidden screen-reader spans, and the gt-accessibility frontend asset bundle. Five public static methods, all exercised. get_aria_sort_attr() covered &mdash; three-branch ternary: column not currently sorted returns aria-sort none (announces the header as sortable but inactive), currently sorted with asc returns aria-sort ascending, currently sorted with desc returns aria-sort descending. Default third-arg branch covered (omitting the dir parameter still routes to ascending via the parameter default). The strict identity check is documented &mdash; uppercase DESC and empty string both fall through to ascending so call sites that pass legacy upper-case or null direction values stay safe. get_visually_hidden_span() covered &mdash; plain text wraps into span class gt-sr-only for the CSS clip-to-1px-box pattern; HTML escaping verified by feeding an injection payload and asserting the raw tags are absent and the entity-encoded form is present (pins the contract against an injection regression); empty string round-trips to an empty span class gt-sr-only. get_aria_label() covered &mdash; plain label emits aria-label Export to CSV; adversarial label with embedded quotes entity-encodes the inner quotes via esc_attr so the attribute boundary cannot be escaped (asserts the inner &amp;quot; substring plus the start/end of the outer quoted attribute). get_aria_describedby() covered &mdash; plain region id emits aria-describedby gt-live-region; adversarial id with attribute-injec