                    <li><strong>5.7.4</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 81 &mdash; pin TC_Wrap_Mode_Service at ~100%). Fourth slice of batch 10. New tests/GTWrapModeServiceTest.php (21 tests / 42 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-wrap-mode-service.php (35 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line + method coverage. TC_Wrap_Mode_Service is the pure-logic helper behind the per-column word-break / hyphenation control feature (#520) &mdash; it exposes the four supported wrap modes (default, break-word, hyphenate, nowrap) plus a sanitization layer for stored settings, the per-mode CSS declaration emitter consumed by the frontend renderer, and the BCP-47 lang resolver used by the hyphenate cell render path. Five public static methods plus the MODES constant, all exercised. get_modes() covered &mdash; returns the four canonical modes in the documented order; constant / getter parity verified so callers reading TC_Wrap_Mode_Service::MODES directly stay in sync with the getter. sanitize() covered &mdash; non-string fallback (null, 123, array, true all collapse to default); whitespace + case normalization via strtolower(trim(...)) (NOWRAP with leading/trailing spaces -&gt; nowrap, Break-Word -&gt; break-word, tab-HYPHENATE-newline -&gt; hyphenate); valid-mode passthrough for all four canonical values; unknown-string fallback to default (empty string, wrap, break_word with underscore). sanitize_map() covered &mdash; non-array guard returns empty array (null, scalar string, integer); default values are intentionally dropped to keep stored settings minimal (matches production comment); non-default values retained; mixed input prunes correctly (col_unknown -&gt; foobar sanitizes to default and is then dropped, demonstrating both layers compose); numeric column ids coerced to strings via the production (string) cast so the returned array keys are always strings even when callers pass integer ids. css_for_mode() covered &mdash; every switch arm exercised: break-w