                    <li><strong>5.7.3</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 80 &mdash; pin TC_Border_Service at ~100%). Third slice of batch 10. New tests/GTBorderServiceTest.php (23 tests / 56 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-border-service.php (35 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line + method coverage. TC_Border_Service is the pure CSS-emitter that generates scoped per-table border styles for four sections (row dividers, column dividers, outer border, header bottom border) and exposes four named presets (classic, rows_only, none, outer_only) consumed by the table-builder admin UI. Three public static methods plus the PRESETS constant, all exercised. get_preset_settings() covered &mdash; the four canonical presets round-trip with their expected enabled / color / width / radius fields (classic uses #dee2e6 on rows/cols/outer + #adb5bd on header bottom; rows_only enables only horizontal dividers + header; none zeroes every section; outer_only is the only preset with a non-zero border-radius of 4px); unknown preset names and the empty-string name both fall back to classic via the ?? null-coalesce. get_border_css() covered &mdash; every section has an enabled vs disabled branch, each one independently exercised. Row dividers: enabled emits border-bottom: {width}px solid {color}; disabled emits border-bottom: none; invalid hex (e.g. not-a-color) falls back to the section default #dee2e6 via the sanitize_hex_color() ?: short-circuit. Column dividers: enabled emits the body rule on td, th plus the :last-child reset that strips the trailing border on the rightmost cell; disabled emits a single border-right: none body rule with no :last-child selector. Outer border: enabled emits border: {w}px solid {c}; border-radius: {r}px with explicit radius; missing radius key falls through absint(null) -&gt; 0px; disabled emits border: none and suppresses the border-radius rule entirely. Header bottom border: enabled emits thead tr border-bottom with the header-sp