                    <li><strong>5.7.2</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 79 &mdash; pin TC_Row_Grouping_Service at ~100%). Second slice of batch 10. New tests/GTRowGroupingServiceTest.php (25 tests / 49 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-row-grouping-service.php (38 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line + method coverage (36/36 lines, 7/7 methods, per isolated --coverage run). TC_Row_Grouping_Service is the pure-logic helper behind the DataTables RowGroup integration: it reads three group_by_* settings keys, buckets a flat row list into a value =&gt; rows[] map, serialises the DataTables rowGroup extension config as JSON, and renders a &lt;tr&gt; group-header row with sanitised label + colspan. Five public static methods plus one private column_index() helper, all exercised. is_enabled() covered &mdash; false when group_by_column is absent or empty; true when populated (the gate the rest of the rowGroup pipeline keys off). get_group_column() covered &mdash; absent setting returns empty string; sanitize_key lowercases + strips non-[a-z0-9_-] characters (Category_2 -&gt; category_2, Col-ID_1!@# -&gt; col-id_1). is_default_collapsed() covered &mdash; false when group_default_collapsed is absent or zero; true for explicit 1 and boolean true. group_rows() covered &mdash; empty input returns empty map; multi-row bucketing preserves insertion order within each group key; rows missing the column key bucket under empty-string key alongside rows with explicit empty value; non-string column values cast via (string) so integer 7 ends up under string key 7. get_datatables_config() covered &mdash; column_index found case (group_by_column category at index 1 in a 3-column array emits dataSrc: 1); not-found case falls back to 0 (the column_index private helper default-return branch); columns array entries without an id key never match; groupCollapsed propagates from is_default_collapsed; structural assertions on the JSON envelope (startClassName gt-row-group-he