                    <li><strong>5.7.1</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 78 &mdash; pin TC_Star_Rating_Service at ~100%; opens batch 10). First slice of batch 10. New tests/GTStarRatingServiceTest.php (28 tests / 65 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-star-rating-service.php (51 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line coverage (49/49 statements; 3/3 methods, per isolated --coverage run). TC_Star_Rating_Service is the pure-logic column-type renderer that converts a numeric rating value (e.g. 3.5) into filled / half / empty SVG stars with full accessibility support (role=img, aria-label, aria-hidden=true on inner SVGs) and a DataTables-compatible numeric sort value. Two public static methods plus one private star_svg() helper, all exercised. render() covered &mdash; wrapper span scaffolding (class=gt-star-rating, role=img, data-rating formatted to 2 decimals, data-max integer); default-max behaviour (omitting the max arg still emits data-max=5); aria-label sprintf path (4.0 out of 5 stars via number_format_i18n and max); full/half/empty branch boundary contract &mdash; diff &gt;= 1.0 -&gt; full (so a rating of exactly 1.0 with max 2 yields 1 full + 1 empty, no half), 0.5 &lt;= diff &lt; 1.0 -&gt; half (rating 0.5 + max 1 yields exactly one half star), diff &lt; 0.5 -&gt; empty (rating 0.49 + max 1 yields exactly one empty); mixed 3.5/5 produces 3 full + 1 half + 1 empty; 5/5 produces 5 full (no half/empty); 0/5 produces 5 empty (no full/half); clamping &mdash; negative rating (-3) clamps to 0 (data-rating=0.00, all empty), rating above max (12.7 with max 5) clamps to max (data-rating=5.00, all full), max=0 clamps up to 1 via max(1, (int) max) so data-max=1; input coercion &mdash; numeric string 4.5 parses through floatval, non-numeric abc collapses to 0; custom options &mdash; default color=#f5a623, empty_color=#d3d3d3, size=1em flow into SVG fill / width / height attributes; overrides (#ff0000, #cccccc, 2rem) replace the defaults; half-star SVG emit