                    <li><strong>5.7.0</strong> &mdash; <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 77 &mdash; pin TC_Multi_Sort_Service at ~100%; CLOSES batch 9). Fifth and final slice of batch 9 (slices 73 to 77, v5.6.6 -&gt; v5.7.0 &mdash; all five small 0% files from this batch now pinned). New tests/GTMultiSortServiceTest.php (30 tests / 35 assertions) pins includes/services/class-tc-multi-sort-service.php (51 statements) from 0% -&gt; ~100% line coverage (49/49 statements; 6/6 methods, per isolated --coverage run). TC_Multi_Sort_Service is the pure-logic helper that powers shift-click multi-column sort (max 3 simultaneous columns, MAX_SORT_COLUMNS contract). Five static methods plus one private helper, no wpdb / no filters / no hooks. is_enabled() covered: default-true when the enable_multi_sort setting is absent (existing tables get the feature automatically); explicit true / false; truthy-string passthrough (yes -&gt; true via (bool) cast); zero-string -&gt; false (PHPs one falsy non-empty string). validate_sort_stack() covered: clean entry passthrough; non-array entry skip (not-an-array, 42); empty column_id skip (empty string, missing key); invalid direction defaults to asc (sideways, empty string, missing); lowercase normalization (DESC -&gt; desc, Asc -&gt; asc); sanitize_key strips uppercase + non-[a-z0-9_-] chars (Field 1! -&gt; field1); cap at MAX_SORT_COLUMNS (3); empty input returns empty. get_datatables_order() covered: column_id resolves to index in a multi-column stack ([[1,asc],[3,desc]]); unknown column skipped via the column_index() false-return; empty stack returns empty-array JSON; empty columns array returns empty-array JSON (every column_id fails to resolve); the default [] columns argument matches explicit-empty (signature default branch). build_order_by() covered: whitelisted columns emit ORDER BY field_1 ASC, field_2 DESC; non-whitelisted (including SQL-injection payloads like evil; DROP TABLE wp_users;--) skipped; empty stack returns empty string; w