                    <li><strong>5.2.5</strong> — <?php _e('Test coverage (slice 33 — pin TC_Dirty_State at ~100%). Second per-file fill of the post-cluster-green phase. TC_Dirty_State (17 statements, 0% in the v5.1.8 baseline) is the smallest 0% file in includes/ per the slice 27 inventory. New tests/GTDirtyStateTest.php (11 tests / 30 assertions) pins get_instance() singleton, get_script() content (every wired event handler including the #159 row-deletion regression guard, save-button selectors, beforeunload lifecycle), and enqueue() four-branch coverage (no screen / wrong screen / handle registered -> wp_add_inline_script / handle missing -> direct &lt;script&gt; echo fallback). Bootstrap does not stub get_current_screen / wp_script_is / wp_add_inline_script, so the test declares lightweight in-file shims keyed by $GLOBALS and drives each branch independently. Shim suite: 737 tests / 1446 assertions -> 748 tests / 1476 assertions (+11 / +30). Stays 0E/0F. Legacy runner 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail green. Vitest 957/957 green. Coverage delta: includes/class-tc-dirty-state.php 0% -> ~100%. No customer-facing runtime change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.2.4</strong> — <?php _e('Security (#1069 — fail-closed permission gate + table-access checks + cap tightening on the AJAX boundary). Closes the five authorization findings from the #1069 audit plus one trailing parity site that slice 31 (#1073 / v5.2.3) left behind in TC_Entry_Service. (1) export_table used current_user_can(read) — every logged-in subscriber could export any form. Replaced with a new dedicated export_gravity_tables capability registered in TC_Capabilities_Service, plus checkTableAccessPermission(form_id, table_id) before any data access so export-capable users cannot enumerate rows from a table they do not have explicit access to. (2) get_filter_suggestions only nonce-checked — any nopriv visitor could enumerate distinct field values for any form_id, including admin-only forms. Added checkTableAccessPermission(form_id) after parameter validation. (3) get_lookup_options had the same shape as #2; same fix. (4) upload_file did no capability check beyond the nonce, so a logged-out visitor with a public-page nonce could POST a file and have it written to the WP uploads directory (subject to wp_check_filetype). Added current_user_can(upload_files) after the nonce check; bails with gt_access_denied/403. (5) checkTableAccessPermission silently returned (allowed access) when the table config row was missing or the JSON settings blob was malformed — orphan form_ids (table config deleted but a shortcode still referencing the form) bypassed the role gate entirely. Both fail-open branches now wp_send_json_error([code => gt_access_denied], 403). The existing role-denied branch also gains the canonical gt_access_denied code for consistency. (6) class-tc-entry-service.php:267-269 routed REMOTE_ADDR / HTTP_REFERER / HTTP_USER_AGENT through gt_request_server_text for slice 31 (#1073) parity — submit_new_entry already used this pattern. New capability: export_gravity_tables is auto-granted to administrators on activation and on the version-upgrade path (ensure_capabilities_for_version); manageable through the existing role-grant admin UI alongside View Tables / Edit Tables. Katie-style customers editor / shop-manager role grants keep working. Customer-visible behaviour change: the fail-closed flip on checkTableAccessPermission means customers with orphan form_ids (table config row deleted but a [gravity_table] shortcode still referencing the form) will now see 403 gt_access_denied instead of silently rendering. This is the correct behaviour (orphan = no explicit config = no access). Repair path is unchanged — admins recreate the table config in the table-builder UI and the shortcode resumes working with the configured role gate enforced. New tests/GTAuthorizationGatesTest.php pins the contract via static scans on class-tc-ajax.php + class-tc-capabilities-service.php + class-tc-entry-service.php (21 tests / 46 assertions). Method-body slicer bounded by the next sibling method declaration to avoid false-passes from neighbour-handler bleed. Shim suite: 716 -> 737 tests, 1400 -> 1446 assertions, 0E/0F maintained. Legacy runner 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail green. Vitest 957/957 green. Patch bump 5.2.3 -> 5.2.4 per the bump-at-9 rule. Audit: github.com/TableCrafter/gravity-tables/issues/1069.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>5.2.3</strong> — <?php _e('Security (#1073 — wp_unslash + sanitize_text_field + per_page cap on the AJAX boundary). The audit on #1073 found four input-sanitization hygiene gaps in includes/class-tc-ajax.php. This release closes all four: (1) submit_new_entry read $_SERVER[REMOTE_ADDR] / HTTP_REFERER / HTTP_USER_AGENT raw before stuffing the values into the GFAPI entry array. Now route through a new gt_request_server_text helper that wraps sanitize_text_field(wp_unslash(...)) and returns the configured default verbatim when the key is missing (proxy environments where REMOTE_ADDR can legitimately be absent). (2) submit_new_entry per-field POST read ($value = $_POST[$input_name]) now runs through wp_unslash before sanitize_field_value, so wp_magic_quotes-added backslashes do not survive into storage. Cardinal regression: O\'Brien round-trips as O\'Brien, not O\\\'Brien. (3) The four legacy stripslashes call sites flagged by the audit (sort_stack at line 1366, drilldown_filters at 1387, filters at 5386, columns at 5387) swap to wp_unslash — wp_magic_quotes-aware and the WP-idiomatic AJAX-boundary choice. (4) get_entries now clamps per_page to [1, 200] via max(1, min(200, ...)), mirroring the TC_Entry_Repository::find and REST per_page idiom. A hostile client can no longer request per_page=999999 and starve the DB. The new helper lives in includes/helpers-request.php and is wired into the plugin bootstrap (tablecrafter.php) alongside the other shared helpers from #1075 / #1076. class-tc-ajax.php also require_once\'s the helper defensively so legacy-runner tests that load the AJAX class directly (test-issue-72 / -78 / -305 / -379) get the dependency too. New tests/GTInputSanitizationTest.php pins the contract (21 tests / 36 assertions): helper unit tests for missing-key default, slash strip, tag strip, normal IP round-trip, apostrophe round-trip; plus static-scan invariants on includes/class-tc-ajax.php proving the four audit sites are patched (no raw $_SERVER reads, gt_request_server_text called 3x, wp_unslash on $_POST[$input_name], zero stripslashes calls left, wp_unslash on sort_stack / drilldown_filters / filters / columns, per_page clamped to [1, 200]). tests/test-issue-568-slice4-drilldown-persistence.php AC#2 updated to assert the wp_unslash idiom. Shim suite: 695 -> 716 tests, 1364 -> 1400 assertions, 0E/0F maintained. Legacy runner 523/523 + 2 allowed-fail green. Vitest 957/957 green. Patch bump 5.2.2 -> 5.2.3 per the bump-at-9 rule. No customer-facing behaviour change. Legitimate inputs round-trip identically (O\'Brien stays O\'Brien; per_page=25 / 50 / 100 still work). The clamp only affects pathological per_page=999999 / per_page=-1 cases the audit called out. Hardening only — no exploitable injection path was demonstrated, but the AC bar "every superglobal read needs wp_unslash" is now met. Audit: github.com/TableCrafter/gravity-tables/issues/1073.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
