                    <li><strong>4.91.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #556): Expandable / collapsible detail rows runtime. Slice 1 (v4.7.49) shipped TC_Detail_Rows_Service. Slice 2 (v4.9.20) shipped the per-column admin toggle + column_detail_only persistence + template config injection — with the orphan invariant "no production caller in frontend.js yet" pinned by docs. Slice 3 (this release) wires the runtime: chevron toggle column emitted in thead + per parent row when at least one column is flagged detail-only; clicking the chevron expands a hidden gt-detail-row sibling rendered immediately after the parent, containing detail-flagged values as a responsive grid of label/value pairs. Keyboard accessible (native button semantics — Enter / Space activate), aria-expanded flips, aria-controls points at the row id, chevron rotates 90deg via CSS transition. Empty-detail rows still get a chevron with "No additional details for this row." in the panel so the UX stays consistent across rows. Zero changes to legacy tables — empty column_detail_only keeps the render identical to v4.90.0. 13 assertions. **Customer-facing**: tables with 10+ columns can hide secondary fields behind a row-click on mobile, preserving the parent layout and only revealing extras on demand. Closes #556 end-to-end.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
