                    <li><strong>4.77.0</strong> — <?php _e('Security feature (CLOSES #806 — HIGH PRIORITY child of #793 audit): GF creditcard field PCI-safe render. Previously the cell render passed $entry[N] (typically empty for composites) through esc_html, the eye popup\'s generic multi-input scanner concatenated every N.1-N.5 sub-input, and the Abilities API query_rows returned raw entries. New TC_Creditcard_Field_Renderer ships render_safe (emits only "Visa ending in 1234" from last 4 digits of N.1), render_safe_full (adds holder name for eye popup), redact_for_payload (scrubs N.1-N.5 from entry shape). Cell renderer / AJAX get_entries / eye popup / Abilities API query_rows all wired. Never reads N.2 / N.3 (full PAN / CVV slots — empty in GF 2.x but defended defensively). Sort / filter / paste / export remain ➖ N/A. 22 new assertions; output guaranteed to contain no digit run longer than 4 chars. **Customer-facing**: tables embedding payment forms can be safely admin-viewed or exposed to MCP / AI tooling without PCI leakage risk.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.76.0</strong> — <?php _e('Audit (slice 3 of N — #793): Filed 5 child issues for Post + Pricing field-type gaps. #806 creditcard HIGH PRIORITY (PCI — must not leak full PAN; covers abilities redaction), #807 product composite render, #808 post_image composite, #809 post_category term-name display, #810 post_content HTML cell strategy. Each child carries AC + TDD plan. Matrix cross-references updated. **No runtime change** — child issues drive the fixes in subsequent iters.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.75.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (CLOSES #797 — child of #793 audit): GF multiselect facet filter + sort key service. New TC_Multiselect_Filter_Service with split_values / distinct_values / row_matches / sort_key. Distinct-value facet matching (OR-match, case-insensitive). First-value sort key with empty-cells-last sentinel. The filter-UI repaint that surfaces distinct-value checkboxes is a downstream JS wiring step — out of scope for this PR. 16 new assertions. All 5 originally-filed #793 child issues are now closed (#795, #796, #797, #798, #799).', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.74.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (CLOSES #798 — child of #793 audit): GF checkbox field renders selected options. Previously cells appeared blank because GF stores each option in a separate sub-input (N.1, N.2, ...) and the bare entry slot is empty. New TC_Checkbox_Field_Renderer collects every non-empty {N}.{integer} sub-input, sorts numerically (preserves form-builder choice order), joins comma-separated. get_entries post-processes the AJAX response; eye popup uses the same render. Defensive: malformed sub-keys (5.foo, 5.1.2) are rejected. 14 new assertions. **Customer-facing**: checkbox columns finally show selected options.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.73.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (CLOSES #796 — child of #793 audit): GF address field renders the full postal block. Previously only street (sub-input N.1) appeared in tables; city / state / zip / country were silently lost. New TC_Address_Field_Renderer composes the six sub-inputs into a postal-layout text block. get_entries post-processes the AJAX response to populate the bare entry slot so the JS renders the full address. Eye popup uses the same postal layout. 16 new assertions. **Customer-facing**: addresses finally display fully in tables and the eye popup — no more silent data loss.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.72.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (CLOSES #799 — child of #793 audit): GF signature field renders as inline <img>. Previously the URL rendered as plain text. New case "signature" branch in TC_Cell_Renderer plus render_signature() helper emits <img class="gt-cell-signature"> with default 40px max-height. Filter gt_signature_max_height overrides. Alt respects context[name] (defaults to "signature"). URL resolved via existing resolve_url helper for AJAX/REST contexts (#606). 9 new assertions. **Customer-facing**: signatures captured via the GF Signature add-on now appear inline in the table instead of as URL text.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.71.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (CLOSES #795 — child of #793 audit): GF list field renders properly. Previously list-field columns rendered as serialised PHP garbage (a:N:{...}) because GF stores list-row-data as serialize($rows) at the bare field-id slot. New TC_List_Field_Renderer (safe unserialize with allowed_classes=false) drives render (HTML table for multi-col, headerless for single-col), eye popup (row-per-line text), and abilities API (query_rows now returns deserialised JSON arrays for list-field values). All cell content escaped via esc_html. 42 new assertions. **Customer-facing**: list fields finally show readable rows in tables and the eye popup; AI tooling via the Abilities API receives structured JSON instead of serialised garbage. Filter / sort / inline edit / paste for list fields remain follow-up scope.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.70.0</strong> — <?php _e('Audit (slice 2 of N — #793): Filed 5 child issues for the worst Standard / Advanced field-type gaps surfaced by the slice-1 matrix. #795 list-as-serialised-PHP (high priority), #796 address renders only street (city/state/zip/country lost), #797 multiselect filter / sort, #798 checkbox composite render, #799 signature inline image. Each child carries AC + TDD slice plan. Matrix cross-references updated. **Customer-facing**: no runtime change yet — this slice queues the per-field fixes; subsequent iters drive them through PR + release per the established loop pattern.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
