                    <li><strong>4.68.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #516): Header-matching column-type preservation for clipboard paste. When the pasted first row is headers AND every header matches one of the table\'s saved column labels (case-insensitive, whitespace-trimmed), the apply path rewires the column-id order to follow the pasted header order. Partial matches return null → falls back to positional. New static helper TC_Clipboard_Paste_Handler::rewire_columns_by_header. Stress invariant: 1000x20 paste parses + rewires under 5s. 12 new assertions. **Customer-facing**: reorder a column in Excel and the next paste still lands in the right Gravity Forms fields.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.67.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slices 2 + 3 — CLOSES #526): Media-folder JS adapter + fallback-image picker + tooltip. Slice 1 (v4.7.41) shipped TC_Media_Folder_Adapter (PHP detection for FileBird / FolderPress / WP Media Folder / Real Media Library). This release ships assets/js/gt-media-folder.js exposing window.GTMediaFolder.openFrame, the enqueue + localize boot, a new "Default image fallback (#526)" group in the table builder with a URL input + "Pick image" button that uses the adapter, and a tooltip that names the active folder plugin (or lists all four supported ones when none is detected). Picked URL is sanitized via esc_url_raw and stored on the table config. **Customer-facing**: admins with FileBird / FolderPress / WP Media Folder / Real Media Library installed now get the folder browser inside Gravity Tables\' image picker. Without any of those plugins, the plain wp.media frame still opens — no regression. 29 new assertions.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.66.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3 — #516): Clipboard paste-from-Excel admin handler. New "Paste data (#516)" group in the table builder with a TSV textarea, headers toggle, append / replace radios, and Preview / Apply buttons. Two AJAX endpoints (gt_clipboard_paste_preview / gt_clipboard_paste_apply) gated on manage_options + nonce. Preview reports rows / cols / detected dialect via slice-1 TC_TSV_Parser_Service. Apply writes via GFAPI::add_entry per row; replace mode trashes existing active entries first. Slice 3 will add column-type preservation + #496 detection integration + stress invariant. **Customer-facing**: copy a range from Excel / Sheets / Numbers, paste into the table builder, click Preview to see the parsed shape, then Apply to ingest the rows.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.65.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #519): Scheduled export admin UI + email + Run-now + filter opt-in. New "Scheduled export (#519)" group in the table builder Display Options with 6 controls (enabled toggle, recurrence selector hourly / 6h / daily / weekly, format selector CSV / XLSX, filename pattern, email recipients, honor-filters toggle) plus a "Run export now" button. AJAX handler ajax_run_now under capability gate manage_options. Email destination via wp_mail attachment when recipients are set. Filter opt-in via new gt_scheduled_export_search_criteria filter hook. save_table reconciles the WP-Cron queue on save. **Customer-facing**: per-table scheduled CSV / XLSX export is now configurable end-to-end from the table builder UI; admins can email exports to a recipient list or write them under uploads/gravity-tables-exports/ on hourly / 6h / daily / weekly cadence.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.64.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3 — #519): Scheduled outbound export runner. Slice 1 (v4.7.37) shipped TC_Export_Filename_Service — pure token expander for filename patterns. Slice 2 (this release) ships the runner: new TC_Scheduled_Export_Service registers a WP-Cron hook (gt_run_scheduled_export), exposes schedule_for_table / clear_schedule_for_table / run_scheduled_export. The cron callback queries entries via GFAPI::get_entries, renders them to CSV (or XLSX when PhpOffice\\PhpSpreadsheet is loaded — falls back to CSV otherwise), and writes the file to wp-content/uploads/gravity-tables-exports/. Failure paths return distinct WP_Error codes (gt_export_not_found / gt_export_unavailable / gt_export_write_failed / gt_export_query_failed / gt_export_invalid_args) and log to error_log so admins find them in debug.log without needing the slice-3 admin notice. Mirrors the inbound counterpart TC_Auto_Import for parity — same 6h custom cron interval, same idempotent schedule_for_table pattern. Slice 3 (deferred): per-table admin settings panel, email destination + recipient list, "Run export now" button, "honors current filters" opt-in. CSV writer passes the PHP 8.5+ $escape arg explicitly to avoid the fputcsv deprecation warning. 56 new assertions in tests/test-issue-519-slice2-scheduled-export-service.php; 368/368 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: not yet — the runner is shipped and bootstrapped, but until slice 3 wires the admin UI the only way to enable a scheduled export is calling TC_Scheduled_Export_Service::schedule_for_table($id, "daily") from a custom snippet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.63.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #503): Abilities Registry write wire-up + premium gating + WP <7.0 admin notice + bootstrap. Closes the three-slice arc for #503. (1) Premium gate in dispatch() fires BEFORE the concrete handler so we never hit GF / DB on the free-tier denial path — free tier returns WP_Error gt_ability_premium_required (status 402) for write abilities; read abilities skip the gate. (2) gravity_tables.update_cell delegates to GFAPI::update_entry after get_entry resolves the row; gravity_tables.create_row delegates to GFAPI::add_entry with form_id resolved from the table binding; gravity_tables.delete_row soft-deletes via GFAPI::update_entry status=trash. (3) New boot() bootstrap hooks register() on init and arms the legacy-WP dismissible admin notice on admin_init. (4) require_once for the registry is back (had been intentionally dropped between slices to avoid loading dead code). (5) New docs/developer/abilities.md documents the dispatch API and the six canonical ability ids with sample invocations. **Customer-facing**: on WP 7.0 sites the platform-level Abilities API now sees Gravity Tables as a first-class participant — external AI tooling can list / read / query (free tier) and update / create / delete (premium) via the standard discovery layer. On WP <7.0 a one-line dismissible notice surfaces in admin so site owners know the integration is dormant. MCP adapter integration is deliberately not in scope — the WP 7.0 MCP spec is still moving; once it stabilizes, a follow-up issue can land transport-specific glue. 40 new assertions in tests/test-issue-503-slice3-writes-and-notice.php; 194 assertions across all three slice suites; 367/367 plugin tests pass.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.62.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3 — #503): Abilities Registry read-only wire-up. Slice 1 (v4.7.31) shipped TC_Abilities_Registry with six canonical ability definitions and stub callbacks returning WP_Error gt_ability_not_wired. Slice 2 wires the three read-only abilities to real handlers: gravity_tables.list_tables (delegates to TC_Admin::get_tables), gravity_tables.get_table_schema (delegates to TC_Admin::get_table + get_table_config), and gravity_tables.query_rows (delegates to GFAPI::get_entries with filter / sort / pagination). New public dispatch(string, array) API routes any ability invocation through validated argument handling; write abilities (update_cell / create_row / delete_row) still return the slice-1 not_wired stub until slice 3 lands premium gating + MCP adapter integration. 48 new assertions plus 106 surviving slice-1 assertions. **Customer-facing**: on WP 7.0 sites with the Abilities API loaded, external AI tooling and MCP clients can now read tables / schemas / rows via the platform-level discovery layer.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.61.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 2 — CLOSES #501): Row Expiry admin opt-in. Slice 1 (v4.7.30) shipped TC_Row_Expiry_Service plus the frontend render gate (applyRowExpiry in assets/js/frontend.js) and the four expiry_* keys round-tripped through sanitizers, shortcode attrs, and the template — but the table-builder UI to set them per-table had been removed without restoration (history at #657). This release adds a new "Row Expiry (#501)" group in Display Options with four controls: an Expiry column dropdown (Date / DateTime / Time fields from the bound Gravity Form), a Behavior selector (Hide / Strikethrough / Move to bottom), a Grace period input (days), and an Inverse-mode checkbox ("show only upcoming"). Values pre-fill from $table_settings; admin.js posts the four keys at top-level of the save payload so they land in $_POST where the existing slice-1 sanitizers already accept them. Admin preview always shows every row regardless. 33 new assertions in tests/test-issue-501-slice2-row-expiry-admin.php. **Customer-facing**: per-table row expiry can now be configured directly in the builder UI — no more shortcode-only / filter-only access.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.60.4</strong> — <?php _e('Bugfix: the entry-detail "eye" popup was rendering "-" for every plain select / radio / checkbox field. Reported on a Load Tracker site where the popup showed the numeric amount but no unit ("Tons", "Yards") for the "Choose Measurement" column. Root cause: Gravity Forms 2.9.29 changed `GFCommon::get_lead_field_display()`\'s signature from `($field, $entry, $currency)` to `($field, $value, $entry, ...)`. Our call site in `TC_Ajax::get_entry_details()` still used the old shape; GF\'s compat wrapper salvaged the currency but fed the entry array into the `$value` slot, which made select-label resolution return nothing. Fixed the call site to pass `($field, $raw, $entry)` per the current signature. Pinned by tests/EntryDetailLeadFieldDisplayCallSignatureTest.php. **Customer-facing**: every plain select / radio / checkbox in the eye popup now displays its actual label instead of a dash.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.60.3</strong> — <?php _e('Bugfix: sticky header silently regressed on sites running aggressive critical-CSS pipelines (NitroPack / WP Rocket) combined with heavy themes (JupiterX + Elementor Canvas). The `sticky_header` toggle stayed checked but the thead no longer froze on scroll. Local reproduction passed cleanly; the failure was production-only. Defensive fix in assets/css/frontend.css: added `position: -webkit-sticky` (older iOS / Safari prefix) and promoted `position: sticky` to `!important` so critical-CSS minifiers cannot strip the declaration and late-loading theme styles cannot override it at equal specificity. The `!important` is on `position`, not `z-index`, so the #617 audit remains clean. Pinned by tests/StickyHeaderDefensivePositionTest.php. **Customer-facing**: the sticky header behaves again on sites where it had silently dropped out.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.60.2</strong> — <?php _e('Two-bug bundle reported by a customer on 2026-05-12. **(A)** The frontend "Add New Entry" popup was unclickable -- every click in the form area dismissed the modal, and on production the popup also appeared fully black. A v4.7.65 regression lowered the modal stacking context (#TB_window z-index) to 9999, below WordPress ThickBox\'s overlay at 100050; the dismiss-layer therefore sat in front of the form, swallowing every click. Fix: keep #TB_window at 9999 (honouring the #617 ceiling) and add a new #TB_overlay rule at 9000 in our stylesheet so the modal sits above the overlay. Pinned by tests/AddEntryPopupZIndexTest.php. **(B)** The "Add New Entry" button itself disappeared on tables that did not have Advanced Filters enabled, because its render block in templates/table.php was nested inside the `if ($show_advanced_filters)` conditional. Extracted the button into its own standalone conditional gated only by `$show_add_entry` + `$user_can_add`. Pinned by tests/AddEntryButtonNotNestedInFiltersTest.php. **Customer-facing**: the button now renders for every table that has it enabled, and clicks inside the popup land on the form fields rather than dismissing the modal.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.60.1</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Modernized the Table Features admin interface. Finalized the structural reorganization of the "Advanced & Export" settings into logical, grid-compliant modules (Security & Advanced, Data & i18n, Print & Export) and refined UI components. Resolved HTML nesting issues that caused layout bleeding, redesigned help tooltip icons for a premium aesthetic (24px size + smooth transitions), and resolved pseudo-element conflicts. Also escaped literal script/style tags in help text to satisfy security regression gates. **Customer-facing**: The admin builder is now more organized, accessible, and visually polished.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.60.0</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer feature: Phase 4 JS test surface, slice 2b (#672). Advances the 100% coverage initiative by providing a robust testing infrastructure for the frontend JavaScript surface. Shipped a JS testing shim (`tests/js/_load-frontend.js`) that dynamically imports `assets/js/frontend.js` into the `jsdom` testing environment, shimmed with jQuery attached to `window`. Migrated shape tests in `totals-reducer.test.js`, `url-filters.test.js`, `pagination-labels.test.js`, and `storage-key.test.js` to perform actual assertions against `GravityTable.prototype` methods. Updated `tools/coverage-gate.php` to merge the JS Clover XML report emitted by `vitest` with the PHP coverage report. Added `assets/js/frontend.js` to `docs/COVERAGE_BASELINE.md` with an initial tested coverage baseline of `12.38%`. Executed `npm test -- --coverage` via the `tools/test-all.sh` suite wrapper, verifying that vitest assertions pass and V8 coverage is tracked properly. No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.59.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4 of 4 — CLOSES #568): Click-to-filter drill-down URL persistence. The final slice for #568 that makes drill-down filters persistent across page reloads and shareable via the URL. Implemented gt_df URL parameter ingestion in templates/table.php to seed initial state. Backend TC_Ajax::get_entries now ingests drilldown_filters and injects secure SQL AND EXISTS clauses into both entry retrieval and count queries, ensuring database-level parity and correct pagination. assets/js/frontend.js updated to sync active filters to the browser address bar via history.pushState and trigger AJAX reloads on filter interaction. 12 new test assertions in tests/test-issue-568-slice4-drilldown-persistence.php verify the end-to-end wiring. **Customer-facing**: filtered table views are now bookmarkable and shareable.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.58.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #549): Cell-level vertical alignment overrides. The final slice for #549 that brings the vertical alignment infrastructure into the admin builder UI and frontend runtime. Users can now override vertical alignment for individual cells via a new floating "Cell Toolbar" in the table builder preview area. Clicking any cell allows visitors to toggle vertical alignment (Top/Middle/Bottom) or revert to column default. Storage uses a nested `cell_vertical_alignments[entry_id][field_id]` map, persisted via TC_Admin::save_table with delegation to TC_Vertical_Align_Service::sanitize_cell_map. templates/table.php now fetches this map and uses TC_Vertical_Align_Service::resolve() to apply correct precedence (Cell > Column > Global). assets/js/frontend.js updated to respect these overrides during AJAX row rendering. 15 new test assertions in tests/test-issue-549-slice3-cell-override.php pin the sanitizer + template resolution + admin toolbar logic + frontend JS sync. 771/771 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: you can now override vertical alignment for individual cells in the table builder.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.57.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #521): Toolbar visibility template wire-up. New $gt_tv_visible closure at the top of templates/table.php consults TC_Toolbar_Visibility_Service::is_visible against $table_config[toolbar_visibility]. Six existing component conditionals AND-extended: global_search (search input), export_buttons (toolbar export buttons block), column_filters (per-column filter row), pagination (controls), length_selector (Show N entries dropdown), info_label (entry-count line). Slice-2 AC#6 retired in same PR. With slice 3, #521 closes end-to-end across 3 slices spanning v4.7.38 → v4.56.0 → v4.57.0. Backwards compatible — legacy gates preserved + default-visible behavior for tables without toolbar_visibility set. 12 new assertions; 756/756 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: unchecking any of the 6 component checkboxes now actually hides that component on the live table.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.56.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3): Toolbar visibility admin opt-in (#521). Slice 1 (v4.7.38) shipped TC_Toolbar_Visibility_Service as a pure config helper for granular per-component toolbar visibility — orphan with zero callers. Slice 2 (this release) wires the admin: 6 checkboxes for global_search / pagination / length_selector / info_label / column_filters / export_buttons in a new "Toolbar visibility" section of Display Options. Sanitizer delegates to ::normalize; admin.js posts the map. Default for unset tables: every component visible (backward-compat). Distinct from legacy show_search / show_pagination booleans which still work — additive + finer-grained. Slice 3 will wire templates/table.php. Loop session ends at this release; handoff at root LOOP_HANDOFF.md. 18 new assertions; 744/744 plugin tests pass. No visual change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.55.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4j of N — feature-complete for #517 / #613 write path): Push-back permission gate. The final layer per #613 roadmap. maybe_pushback_to_airtable now does a current_user_can check at the very TOP of the helper — before rate limiter, conflict pre-fetch, and write. Default cap manage_options; filterable via gt_airtable_writeback_capability (e.g. edit_others_posts for editor-role write). Denied path: appends "direction => denied" event to audit log + safe_log + return; (no rate-limit consumption, no HTTP). Audit log now distinguishes FOUR push outcomes: push, conflict, throttled, denied. With slice 4j, all 7 layers from #613 scope are wired (sync_direction + record-id mapping + audit log + conflict resolution + rate limiting + permission gate). 16 new assertions; 726/726 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: non-privileged users can no longer trigger Airtable writes; admins see denied events in audit log.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.54.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4i of N): Airtable rate-limiter wire-up (#517 / #613). Slice 4h shipped the limiter as orphan; slice 4i (this release) wires it. In maybe_pushback_to_airtable: BEFORE any HTTP call, consult should_throttle. If at-or-above the 5 req/s per-base cap, append "direction => throttled" event to audit log + safe_log warning + return; (no HTTP). AFTER each HTTP call (fetch_single_record + update_record), record_request to track the bucket. Local GFAPI update already succeeded; only the upstream push gets deferred. Customers can re-trigger by editing again once the window slides forward (~1s). Slice-4h AC#10 retired in same PR. 13 new assertions; 710/710 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: push-back defers gracefully instead of hitting Airtable 429s. Audit log distinguishes push / conflict / throttled.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.53.0</strong> — <?php _e('Bugfix + Feature. Bugfix: Airtable submenu link in the admin menu pointed at /wp-admin/gravity-tables-airtable (404) instead of /wp-admin/admin.php?page=gravity-tables-airtable. Root cause: priority collision between the parent menu registration and the submenu hook (both at default priority 10; order depended on file load). Fix: explicit priority 20 on the submenu hook. Feature (slice 4h of N): Airtable rate-limiter service (#517 / #613). Pure per-base sliding-window rate limiter that protects against 429 Too Many Requests (Airtable: ~5 req/s per base). Public API: should_throttle, record_request, option_key (per-base, sanitized), max_requests_per_window (=5), window_seconds (=1), clear. Per-base option storage; reader/writer/deleter callables injectable. Sliding window prunes expired timestamps on every read/write. Per-base isolation. Orphan-with-test-contract: AC#10 pins no production caller yet; slice 4i wires into push helper. 27 new assertions; 695/695 plugin tests pass. No customer-facing change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.52.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4g of N): Airtable conflict-detector wire-up — optimistic locking for push-back (#517 / #613). Slice 4f shipped the detection helpers as orphan; slice 4g (this release) wires them. In maybe_pushback_to_airtable, before update_record: fetch_single_record to read current Airtable lastModifiedTime, compare against local baseline via detect_conflict. On conflict: append "direction => conflict" event to audit log + skip update_record. On no-conflict: proceed; AFTER successful update, snapshot the new lastmod as baseline. Probes canonical field names (Last Modified Time / Last Modified / Modified / Updated / Updated At). Fail-open semantics preserved. Slice-4f AC#7 retired in same PR. 13 new assertions; 668/668 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: pushes skip silently-conflicting overwrites; admins see conflicts in the audit log.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.51.1</strong> — <?php _e('Bugfix: Admin builder page truncated past Display Options. A translatable help-text span in admin/views/table-builder.php (Print settings master toggle) contained a literal &lt;style media="print"&gt; token; PHP echoed it verbatim, browser parsed it as a real opening style tag mid-page and ate the rest of the document as CSS. Symptom: Display Options rendered, then nothing — the rest of the builder UI silently vanished. Side-effect: WP core Underscore.js Site Icon template leaked through producing a {{ data.url }} 404. Fix: replace &lt; / &gt; with HTML entities. 4 more instances of the same pattern audited and fixed in admin/views/documentation.php. New regression test sweeps both view files. 655/655 plugin tests pass.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
