                    <li><strong>4.46.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4a of N): Airtable update-record (PATCH) method (#517 / #613 territory). Slices 1-3b shipped the Airtable READ path end-to-end. Slice 4a (this release) ships the WRITE half: TC_Airtable_Sync_Engine::update_record(base, table, record_id, fields, token, [http]) builds the URL via the slice-1 builder, posts a PATCH with Bearer auth + JSON body {fields: {...}} via wp_remote_request, returns the same structured shape as the read methods. Fail-closed: empty token / invalid record id / empty fields all refuse without firing HTTP. Orphan-with-test-contract: AC#9 pins the slice-4b orphan invariant. Slice 4b will add per-table sync_direction admin option (pull_only / push_only / two_way) and wire gt_update_entry AJAX to PATCH-push when applicable. Slice 4c+ adds conflict resolution, rate limiting, audit log per #613 roadmap. 23 new assertions; 543/543 plugin tests pass. No customer-facing change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.45.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of N): Vertical alignment service production wire (#549). Slice 1 (v4.7.48) shipped TC_Vertical_Align_Service as a pure resolver helper — fully orphan with zero callers. Slice 2 (this release) wires it into production: the column_vertical_alignments sanitizer now sources its whitelist from ::alignments() (source of truth in one place); the template emits a service-derived class via ::to_class() (gt-valign-top / gt-valign-bottom; middle has no class because that\'s the browser default) ADDITIONALLY to the existing inline-style emission (purely additive — backwards compatible with custom CSS that relies on inline styles). CSS rules already shipped in slice 1.2. Slice 3 will ship the cell-override UX (per-cell toolbar that lets a visitor override the column-level alignment). 9 new assertions; 520/520 plugin tests pass. No visual change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.44.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #553): WAF-safe payload client-side encode. templates/table.php applies the gt_waf_safe_payload_enabled filter (default false) and exposes the result as waf_safe_payload in $table_config. assets/js/frontend.js reads the flag at the gt_update_entry (per-field) + gt_update_entry_fields (bulk) call sites; when on, JSON.stringify + btoa-encodes the payload (entry_id + table_id + updates / fields) and posts an opaque base64 envelope under `payload`. Server (slice 2 v4.41.0) already accepts both shapes. Customers behind aggressive WAFs (Cloudflare, Sucuri, mod_security, Wordfence) opt in via add_filter(\'gt_waf_safe_payload_enabled\', \'__return_true\') so generic SQLi/XSS rules can\'t pattern-match cell content. Slice-2 AC#6 retired in same PR. With slice 3, #553 closes end-to-end across 3 slices spanning v4.7.22 → v4.41.0 → v4.44.0. 15 new assertions; 511/511 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: single-filter opt-in for sites where WAFs false-positive on inline-edit payloads.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.43.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 3 of 3 — CLOSES #544): Multi-row sticky header CSS emission. templates/table.php calls TC_Sticky_Rows_Service::frozen_count to read the count, then when > 1 builds inline CSS scoped to #table_instance_id with `position: sticky` + accumulated `top: calc(var(--gt-sticky-row-height, 38px) * (N-1))` + z-index ladder for each thead tr:nth-child(N) th. Single-row sticky stays on the existing v4.7.46 path. Customers can override row height per-table via --gt-sticky-row-height. Combined with gt-freeze-first-column (#534) for Excel-style top-left freeze. Slice-2 AC#5 retired in same PR. With slice 3, #544 closes end-to-end across 3 slices spanning v4.7.46 → v4.42.0 → v4.43.0. 10 new assertions; 496/496 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: multi-row thead tables now show multiple frozen rows during scroll.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.42.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3): Multi-row sticky header admin opt-in (#544). Slice 1 (v4.7.46) shipped TC_Sticky_Rows_Service as a pure config helper (clamps frozen_top_rows 1..10) — fully orphan with zero callers. Slice 2 (this release) adds the "Number of header rows to freeze" number input next to the existing "Sticky header" checkbox in Display Options, wires admin.js to post the value, and adds an apply_v48_v49_sanitizers block that delegates clamping to TC_Sticky_Rows_Service::normalize. PHP view pre-fills the input value (parity with sticky_header). Slice 3 will emit per-N CSS so multiple thead rows stay sticky with accumulated top offsets, combined with freeze-first-column (#534) for an Excel-style top-left freeze. 17 new assertions; 486/486 plugin tests pass. No customer-facing change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
