                    <li><strong>4.39.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2 of 3): Click-to-filter cell drill-down per-column admin opt-in (#568). Slice 1 (v4.7.53) shipped TC_Drilldown_Filter_Service as a pure helper (filter-state with toggle, AND-apply, URL serde) — fully orphan with zero callers. Slice 2 (this release) wires the per-column "Enable click-to-filter" checkbox + admin.js (boolean per-field <-> flat list of field_ids round-trip) + AJAX sanitizer (delegates to service::normalize_settings). Slice 3 will ship the frontend cell-click delegation + removable filter chips above the table + URL persistence via the slice-1 serde. Distinct from #373 per-column dropdown filters: drill-down is "filter by example" on a value you can see, not a list to choose from. 11 new assertions; 447/447 plugin tests pass. No runtime change yet.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.38.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 4 of N — CLOSES #518): Rowspan auto-merge live runtime via AJAX response + JS renderer. AJAX response shape now includes `directives` (per-column [row_idx => {render, rowspan}] map computed via TC_Rowspan_Merge_Service). JS renderer in templates/table.php consumes the directives: skips <td> when render=false (prior row\'s rowspan covers), emits rowspan="N" when render=true && rowspan>1. With slice 4, #518 ships end-to-end — auto-merge configured in builder shows merged cells in BOTH preview AND live AJAX-rendered tables. Runs are page-scoped (pagination breaks runs). Slice-3 AC#7 retired in same PR. 14 new assertions; 436/436 plugin tests pass. **Customer-facing**: #518 fully end-to-end functional.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
