                    <li><strong>4.19.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Per-table password protection — slice 3 of 3 (#607). The frontend gate. Closes #607 fully end-to-end. Visitors with a password-protected table now see a password form instead of the table; correct entry reveals it for ~24h via signed cookie. Three paths: (1) Forget-password GET ?gt_pw_forget=<id> clears cookie. (2) POST verifies via TC_Table_Password_Service::verify, mints signed token via generate_unlock_token (using wp_salt(auth) as secret), setcookie\'s for 24h. (3) Cookie path delegates to is_unlocked. WP nonce protects POST. Defense in depth: gate fires after settings JSON decode but BEFORE any data fetch / template include — table data never enters HTML when locked. Form input is type="password" autocomplete="current-password" with hidden table_id + nonce fields. 19 new test assertions; 322/322 tests pass. With slices 1 (v4.10.1) + 2 (v4.18.0) + 3 (this release) all shipped, the feature is end-to-end functional. Customer-visible behavior change: tables with a password now block visitors.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.18.0</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Per-table password protection slice 2 of 3 (#607). Wires the admin "Password (optional)" field on the table builder + AJAX save sanitization. Slice 1 (v4.10.1) shipped TC_Table_Password_Service with bcrypt hash/verify; slice 2 (this release) makes it persistable from the admin UI. New "Password protection (#607)" feature group in Display Options. Input is type="password" with autocomplete="new-password". Three sanitizer paths: empty = preserve existing, non-empty = hash + store, sentinel "__GT_CLEAR__" = remove. Hash never echoed back to the browser. Sanitizer in apply_v48_v49_sanitizers delegates to TC_Table_Password_Service::hash. Settings key: table_password_hash. Slice 3 (frontend gate — visitor sees password form, signed-cookie verification, table data stays out of HTML when locked) is still owed; this release stores the password but does NOT yet block visitors. 14 new test assertions; 321/321 tests pass. Customer-visible UI change: new field on the table builder.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.17.0</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer feature: Phase 4 JS test surface slice 2a (#672). Grows JS suite from 2 to 5 starter tests + wires `npm test` into tools/test-all.sh. New shape tests: totals-reducer (Sum/Avg/Min/Max/Count/Count distinct), storage-key (localStorage key derivation), pagination-labels (label resolution + interpolation). tools/test-all.sh now runs `npm test --silent` after the PHP suite when package.json + node_modules are both present; skip-mode (clean exit) when node_modules missing — keeps loop velocity up. Slice 2b pending: replace shape tests with real frontend.js method tests via IIFE shim, extend tools/coverage-gate.php for JS clover. 12 new test assertions; 320/320 plugin tests pass. No GitHub Actions involvement. No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
