                    <li><strong>4.13.3</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer fix (#682): bootstrap WP_INT_TEST guard for Elementor file-top hook registration. tests/bootstrap.php requires tablecrafter.php which load-time-includes class-tc-elementor.php, whose file-top block calls did_action() + add_action() to wire the Elementor widgets/register hook. Under PHPUnit + WP_Mock those WP functions don\'t exist when the require chain runs, so phpunit fataled. Fix wraps the block with !defined(WP_INT_TEST) || !WP_INT_TEST. Production loads still register the hook. 6 new test assertions; 316/316 plugin tests pass. Unblocks vendor/bin/phpunit end-to-end runs (combined with #679 composer.lock + #670 shim + #668 coverage tooling). Phase 2a #669 (baseline report) is now a fast follow-up. No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.13.2</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer fix (#684): tools/freemius-release.sh switched from HMAC-developer-scope signing to Bearer-auth + product-scope endpoints. The dashboard\'s product Settings page exposes pk_/sk_ keys (developer-scope HMAC) and an API Bearer Token (product-scope REST). The HMAC path returned HTTP 401 against product-scope keys. New endpoints: POST /v1/products/<id>/tags.json (upload) + PUT /v1/products/<id>/tags/<tag_id>.json with body {"release_mode":"released"}. Credential file simplified to FS_BEARER_TOKEN + FS_PLUGIN_ID. tools/freemius-sign.php (HMAC helpers) preserved for any future developer-scope use case but no longer the primary path. 22 new test assertions; 315/315 plugin tests pass. Also: LOOP_STRATEGY.md updated with rule #15 (automated tests are the only merge gate, no human-review required) and rule #16 (small + frequent, default ScheduleWakeup 1200s, target ≤20 min wall-clock per iteration). No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.13.1</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer fix (#679): regenerate composer.lock to match composer.json. Lock had drifted — Freemius SDK was 2.13.0 but constraint had bumped to ^2.13.1, and dev-deps (phpunit/phpunit, mockery/mockery, 10up/wp_mock) weren\'t in the lock at all. `composer install --dev` now works on a clean checkout, vendor/bin/phpunit is installed (9.6.34), end-to-end PHPUnit shim from #670 starts working. 12 new test assertions pin the lock-file contract. 315/315 tests pass. Follow-up #682 tracks the remaining bootstrap-vs-WP-Mock-loading-order issue. No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.13.0</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer feature: Phase 2b of the 100% coverage initiative (#670). PHPUnit shim that lets the existing 313+ custom-runner test-issue-*.php suite drive PHPUnit\'s coverage instrumentation, so the pipeline #668 stood up starts producing real coverage data. tests/PHPUnitShimTest.php is a TestCase with a @dataProvider yielding every test-issue file path; for each file, resets the runner globals, sets TC_PHPUNIT_SHIM, requires the file, asserts $failed === 0 + $passed > 0. tests/helpers/runner.php\'s shutdown function early-returns when the shim flag is set (without that, every loaded file would terminate PHPUnit mid-suite). The original `php tests/test-issue-NNN.php` invocations and `tools/test-all.sh` are unchanged — the shim is opt-in via the constant. 14 new test assertions; 314/314 plugin tests pass. Follow-up #679 tracks the composer.lock regeneration needed for end-to-end PHPUnit runs. No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.12.0</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer feature: Phase 1 of the 100% coverage initiative (#668). Wires PHPUnit\'s <coverage> configuration into phpunit.xml.dist, ships tools/coverage.sh as the local entry point, and documents install + run in docs/COVERAGE.md. Backend choice: pcov preferred (10x faster than Xdebug), Xdebug as fallback. Reports: build/coverage/html/ (HTML), build/coverage/clover.xml (for the loop-driven gate #671), and a stdout text summary. Coverage scope: includes/, templates/, admin/, plugin entry; excludes vendor/, build/, node_modules/, tests/, tools/. 19 new test assertions pin every artifact. First run will report near-zero because the 313 existing test-issue-*.php files use the custom gt_assert/describe/it runner, not PHPUnit\'s TestCase — closing that gap is Phase 2b (#670). No customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.11.0</strong> — <?php _e('Maintainer feature: Local-shell Freemius release automation. Replaces the prior browser-driven dashboard flow with tools/freemius-release.sh + tools/freemius-release.php + tools/freemius-sign.php. Signs requests per Freemius\'s HMAC-SHA256 scheme (METHOD\\nCONTENT_MD5\\nCONTENT_TYPE\\nDATE\\nPATH; base64-url-encoded HMAC; FS or FSP Authorization prefix), uploads the built zip via multipart POST to /v1/developers/<id>/plugins/<id>/tags.json, then PUTs {"is_released":true} on the new tag. Credentials sourced from ~/.config/gravity-tables/freemius.env or .freemius-release.env (gitignored). --dry-run prints the planned curl invocations without making the API call. 163 signing-helper assertions + 19 integration assertions cover the help text, missing-creds error path, dry-run plan output, and zip-not-found error path. Also retires the prior ".20 cap" versioning rule for standard semver per Freemius\'s documented expectation: minor for new features, patch for bug fixes, major for breaking changes. v4.10.1 was a misclassification (new feature shipped as patch); v4.11.0 going forward applies semver correctly. No customer-facing runtime change in this release.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.10.1</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 1 of N): Per-table password protection — foundational service (#607). First PR-based iteration under the new TDD + PR-only workflow. Ships TC_Table_Password_Service: bcrypt password hash + verify, deterministic cookie naming (gt_table_pw_<id>), and HMAC-signed unlock-token generation that lets a visitor cookie verify against the current stored hash without a server-side session table. Token format <issued_at>.<base64url(hmac_sha256(table_id|stored_hash|issued_at, secret))>. Rotating the password (or the site secret) invalidates every existing token; clock-skew rejects future-issued tokens; constant-time hash_equals comparison; expired tokens rejected at issued_at + ttl. 38/38 service tests pass. No production wiring yet — slice 2 will add the admin "Password (optional)" field; slice 3 will wire the frontend gate. Customers see no behavior change in v4.10.1.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.10.0</strong> — <?php _e('Minor bump per the .20 cap rule (final v4.9.x patch was v4.9.20). UX polish: the "Recent Versions" list in this docs viewer was now 38+ entries long, forcing customers to scroll a wall of text. Collapsed by default to the 5 most recent versions; click "Show full version history" to expand. Self-contained inline IIFE handles the toggle (adds/removes the gt-recent-collapsed attribute on the <ul>; CSS hides all but the first 5 items when the attribute is set). The button label flips between "Show full version history" and "Show recent only" so the toggle direction is clear. Pure UX polish; no runtime or admin behavior changes. The full per-version list is still here in the source — just visually folded by default.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
