                    <li><strong>4.9.19</strong> — <?php _e('Discovery: dismissible "What\'s new in v4.9.x" admin notice on the tables-list page. After 19 patch iterations across the v4.8.x/v4.9.x audit thread, customers had no clear pointer to the new features. New notice block lists 8 customer-facing improvement areas (Bulk migration, multi-column sort, layout controls, filter persistence, cell types, SEO/accessibility, defensive guard, pagination labels) + "View highlights →" deep-link to admin.php?page=gravity-tables-docs#whats-new. Per-user dismissal via gt_v49_highlights_dismissed user_meta; AJAX handler in tablecrafter.php persists the click. Customers discovering the plugin for the first time see what shipped recently; admins who already know can dismiss in one click.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.18</strong> — <?php _e('Housekeeping + docs polish: closed 14 resolved implementation issues on the GitHub tracker (#650, #651, #652, #653, #654, #655, #656, #657, #658, #659, #661, #662, #663, #664) — each had been wired in production across the v4.7.197-v4.8.13 audit thread but stayed open in the tracker. Plus added a curated "v4.9.x customer-facing highlights" subsection at the top of the in-admin What\'s New block: eight bullet groups summarizing the directly customer-facing improvements landed across v4.8.x and v4.9.x. The existing per-version list stays as the deeper-detail reference. Pure documentation + tracker hygiene; no code changes.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.17</strong> — <?php _e('Feature (slice 2b): Bulk-import-bundle admin form (#522). Closes #522 fully — round-trip migration (Export → Import) now in production. New "Import bundle" button on the tables-list page expands a <details> block with file upload + conflict-resolution policy (Skip / Overwrite / Create as new). admin-post handler does permissions + nonce, validates schema via service::validate, checks compatibility via is_compatible(), iterates tables[], routes each via service::resolve_conflict to insert / update / skip. 5-minute result transient drives a post-redirect notice with {created, updated, skipped, failed} counts. Use "Create as new" for cross-site migration to avoid id collisions.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
