                    <li><strong>4.9.15</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Visitor-side length selector ("Show N entries" dropdown). Closes the length_selector gap from TC_Toolbar_Visibility_Service\'s canonical 6-component list (the other 5 mapped to existing toggles; length_selector had no existing setting). New "Show length selector" checkbox + CSV options input in Display Options. Default options 10/25/50/100/All; -1 = All. Template emits a <select> inside .gt-pagination-container before .gt-pagination-info. frontend.js mutates this.config.per_page on change. Sanitizer accepts -1 sentinel + 1-100000 ints; dedupes. Off by default — existing tables stay locked to the admin-set page size.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.14</strong> — <?php _e('Defensive fix: TC_Data_Integrity_Guard wired into the AJAX save path (#557). The service shipped from v4.7.24 with 19 passing tests as a runtime guard against silent / catastrophic data loss on table save (mirrors competitor failure modes — Supsystic-style "Lost all my tables" 1-star reviews). The docblock said the guard "is invoked from the AJAX save handler BEFORE any UPDATE" — but until v4.9.14 nothing invoked it. New code in TC_Ajax::save_table() before the save call: when updating, fetch the existing-table snapshot, compare incoming payload via assert_safe_table_save. When the service flags a destructive shape (empty title overwriting populated; missing columns when existing had >0), abort with HTTP 409 + the error envelope. Paranoid by design — false positives are recoverable, false negatives are catastrophic.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.13</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Whole-table collapsible toggle (#177). TC_Collapsible_Service shipped with 14 passing tests, an accessible toggle-button HTML emitter, body-wrapper attrs emitter, and an inline-script with localStorage persistence — but no production caller. New "Collapsible table" feature group in Display Options with two checkboxes (Make collapsible + Default to collapsed). Sanitizer in apply_v48_v49_sanitizers. Template emits via service\'s get_toggle_button_html + get_body_wrapper_attrs and wraps the gt-table-wrapper. Self-contained IIFE handles click toggle + localStorage; deliberately avoids the service\'s DataTable.columns.adjust call (plugin doesn\'t use DataTables for own tables). CSS for chevron + body[hidden] respects prefers-reduced-motion. Off by default — existing tables unchanged.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.12</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Persistent filter state via browser localStorage (closes a v4.9.4 docs-sweep flag). New per-table "Persist filters in browser localStorage" toggle in Display Options. When on, visitor\'s search box value + per-column filter selections save to localStorage on every mutation; restored on next visit before the first AJAX. Sort state is intentionally NOT persisted (transient; v4.9.11 default-sort handles initial sort). URL pre-filters take precedence — restore merges, doesn\'t replace. Four new methods: _filterStateStorageKey, persistFilterStateLocal, restoreFilterStateLocal, clearFilterStateLocal. Wired into search handlers + applyAdvancedFilter + clearFilters. Off by default — existing tables unchanged.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.11</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Per-table default sort column + direction admin UI. TC_Default_Sort_Service shipped with 18 passing tests (#115 + #391) but no production caller — the GravityTable JS constructor hardcoded date_created/desc as the universal initial sort. New "Default sort" feature group in Display Options between Pagination Labels and Multi-column Sort. Two controls: column dropdown (driven by form fields, same pattern as Top-N) + direction (Asc/Desc). Sanitizer in apply_v48_v49_sanitizers. Template injects via service\'s get_sort_column/direction. frontend.js init() overrides this.sortField/sortOrder/sortStack from config when default_sort_column is set, before the first loadEntries(). Empty falls through to legacy default. 18/18 service tests still pass.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.10</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Per-table row height + header height + overflow mode admin UI. TC_Row_Height_Service shipped with 21 passing tests, three named presets (compact / default / comfortable), CSS-value validator, and a get_css emitter, but no production caller. New "Row height" feature group in Display Options between URL pre-filtering and Border style: three controls — body row height + header row height (preset name or CSS value) + overflow mode (Ellipsis / Expand). Sanitizer in apply_v48_v49_sanitizers helper. Template emits scoped inline style with the same #gt-table-{id} → #table_instance_id string-replace bridge that v4.9.3 Border preset uses. Mobile cards mode (≤ 768px) reverts to auto. Slice 1 limitation: overflow_mode=expand has no JS click handler yet — behaves like ellipsis until the toggle ships. 21/21 service tests still pass.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.9</strong> — <?php _e('Refactor: extracted v4.8.x / v4.9.x feature sanitizers from save_table() into a new private apply_v48_v49_sanitizers helper. Test #468 enforces a 20k-char locality window for wp_cache_delete; each new sanitizer over the v4.8.x/v4.9.x audit thread pushed closer to the cap (failed twice in v4.9.7 + v4.9.8). After this refactor, save_table → wp_cache_delete distance dropped from 20,019 to 11,585 chars (8,415 chars of headroom). Sanitizer logic is byte-identical to v4.9.8 — only the location moved. Future iterations can add sanitizer blocks without re-trimming comments. Pure refactor, zero customer-facing change.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
                    <li><strong>4.9.8</strong> — <?php _e('Feature: Per-column totals-row aggregation. The legacy show_column_totals feature hardcoded a Sum-only reducer for numeric columns. TC_Formula_Service::SUPPORTED_AGGREGATIONS is [SUM, AVG, MIN, MAX, COUNT, COUNT_DISTINCT] with 22 passing tests but the JS totals-row renderer never used it. New "Totals row aggregation" select in the field-config modal General tab — Auto / Sum / Average / Min / Max / Count / Count distinct. Sanitizer whitelists against SUPPORTED_AGGREGATIONS. frontend.js::updateColumnTotals reads per-column override and applies the matching reducer. Empty per-column override falls through to legacy auto-Sum-for-numeric. Aggregation runs over currently-loaded rows (per-page when pagination is on); server-side full-result-set aggregation is future work.', 'tc-data-tables'); ?></li>
